(23, 2, '2011-03-28 14:30:19', '2011-03-28 14:30:19', '<p>Use este mapa interactivo para encontrar una escuela charter en su comunidad.<br /><br /></p>\n\n<div align="left"><a href="http://app.ccsa.org/apps/mapapp/map.aspx?Zip=&amp;Distance=10&amp;County="><img alt="school_finder.jpg (Entry Feature Thumbnail)" src="/assets_c/2011/03/school_finder-cropped-proto-custom_6.jpg" class="mt-image-none" style="" width="500" height="344" /></a></div>\n\n<p><a href="http://app.ccsa.org/apps/mapapp/map.aspx?Zip=90063&amp;Distance=10&amp;County=">California Charter Schools Association School Finder</a></p>\n\n<div><br /></div>\n', 'Encuentre una escuela charter', 'Use este mapa interactivo para encontrar una escuela charter en su comunidad.\n', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'encuentre_una_escuela_charter', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:14:45', '2016-01-13 04:14:45', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/encuentre_una_escuela_charter/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(24, 2, '2011-03-28 14:43:24', '2011-03-28 14:43:24', '<p><img alt="kid-at-desk.jpg" src="/images/kid-at-desk.jpg" width="250" height="375" class="mt-image-right" style="float: right; margin: 0 0 20px 20px;" />\nMany parents and students choose charter schools because they are seeking a better education and they are dissatisfied with the status quo of traditional education. Charter schools offer a wide variety of learning environments. Some have a theme or specialized curriculum; others focus on fundamentals. Some charter schools look like traditional public schools; others offer online classes and may not even have a physical campus. What all charters have in common is that they are places where meaningful parental involvement is encouraged and valued, and teachers are free to do what they do best - teach. And as public schools, every charter school is open to the entire community and tuition-free.\nHere are some key questions to ask when you\'re choosing a school.</p>\n\n<h2>Identify your family\'s educational priorities</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>What is your child\'s learning style?</li>\n<li>Does he/she do best in small groups?</li>\n<li>Does your child have an interest in the arts?</li>\n<li>Would he/she benefit from an independent study school?\nThese are just some of the options available at charters.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Making the Decision</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Do research by reading school information.</li>\n<li>Visit the school and talk to teachers.</li>\n<li>Watch the teachers in action with students.</li>\n<li>Pay attention to the student-to-teacher ratio.</li>\n<li>Always feel free to ask questions</li>\n<li>One of the best ways to learn about a school is to ask other parents - How do they feel about the School? Are the teachers effective?\nFinally, a majority of charter schools ask parents to be involved in the school community. Inquire about volunteer hours and opportunities at the school.\n<a href="http://www.ccsa.org/2010/09/fact-sheet-for-parents-about-charter-schools.html">Get a fact sheet about charter schools.</a>\n<a href="/2010/12/charter-schools-public-school-reinvented.html">Read about some of the advantages of charter schools.</a></li>\n</ul>\n', 'How to choose the right school for your child', 'Many parents and students choose charter schools because they are seeking a better education and they are dissatisfied with the status quo of traditional education. Use this guide to find the school that is the best fit for your child.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'how_to_choose_the_right_school_for_your_child', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:14:45', '2016-01-13 04:14:45', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/how_to_choose_the_right_school_for_your_child/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
