(153, 2, '2012-09-24 15:08:36', '2012-09-24 15:08:36', '<div class="figure embedded-image none"><img alt="voter_guide_promo_pic.jpg (Entry/Page Lead Image)" src="/assets_c/2012/09/voter_guide_promo_pic-cropped-proto-ftc_theme___lead.jpg" width="612" height="269" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></div>\n\n<p>FTC has created easy-to-read, nonpartisan voter guides to help you learn more about the candidates running for school board in a variety of communities across the state. Find out where candidates stand on education so that you can make informed decisions when you cast your ballot.\nFTC\'s <a href="/2012/07/families-that-can-launches-the-civics-campaign.html">CIVICS campaign</a> is a statewide, non-partisan effort to encourage voter participation in the upcoming elections. Sometimes voters lack the information they need to make decisions about candidates, especially in local elections. This year, Families That Can asked candidates in a variety of school board races across the state to share their views on education. Their responses were gathered and packaged into our handy nonpartisan voter guides to help educate voters about their choices. "Non-partisan" means these guides were not developed to promote specific candidates or viewpoints. Share these voter guides with your friends and family members so that they can become informed voters, too!\n- <a href="/natomas_voter_guide_9-24-12.pdf">Voter Guide - Natomas Unified School District, Sacramento</a>\n- <a href="/San_Juan_Unified_voter_guide_9-24-12.pdf\n">Voter Guide - San Juan Unified School District, Sacramento</a>\n- <a href="/Chico_%20Unified_voter_guide_9-25-12.pdf">Voter Guide - Chico Unified School District, Butte County</a>\n- <a href="/oakland_unified_voter_guide_final_9-27-12.pdf">Voter Guide - Oakland Unified School District</a>\n- <a href="/voter_guide_san_diego_unified_board_district_e_10-24-12.pdf">Voter Guide - San Diego School District - Board District E</a>\nMore guides coming soon!</p>\n', 'Non-partisan Voter Guides for November 6, 2012 School Board Elections', 'Families That Can has created easy-to-read, nonpartisan voter guides to help you learn more about the candidates running for school board in various communities across the state.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'non-partisan_voter_guides_for_november_6_2012_school_board_elections', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:52', '2016-01-13 04:19:52', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/non-partisan_voter_guides_for_november_6_2012_school_board_elections/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(154, 2, '2012-09-25 13:32:20', '2012-09-25 13:32:20', '<p>Rosa Vargas, who grew up in Oakland, shares why she chose to send her children to charter schools instead of to Oakland Unified district schools. Her oldest son attended American Indian and two younger children currently attend Oakland Charter Academy.</p>\n\n<div class="video-container"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/KmYOeiTaGwM" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n\n<p>She also recorded a video in Spanish to share with other parents.</p>\n\n<div class="video-container"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/WegDGC1TZgw" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n', 'Video: "I didn\'t want my children to be a drop out like me"', 'Rosa Vargas, who grew up in Oakland, shares why she chose to send her children to charter schools instead of to Oakland Unified district schools.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'video_i_didnt_want_my_children_to_be_a_drop_out_like_me', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:52', '2016-01-13 04:19:52', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/video_i_didnt_want_my_children_to_be_a_drop_out_like_me/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(155, 2, '2012-09-25 13:39:01', '2012-09-25 13:39:01', '<p>Rosa Vargas es madre de dos estudiantes en Oakland Charter Academy. Comparte sus experiencias con las escuelas charter.\nRosa Vargas maneja largas distancias cada d√≠a para que sus hijos puedan asistir a una escuela ch√°rter. Dice que vale la pena y alenta a los otros padres conocer sus opciones de escuela. Rosa es madre de dos estudiantes en Oakland Charter Academy.</p>\n\n<div class="video-container"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/WegDGC1TZgw" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n\n<p>Tambi√©n aparece en este un video en ingl√©s.</p>\n\n<div class="video-container"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/KmYOeiTaGwM" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n', 'Voces de los Padres: "Las escuelas ch√°rter se enfocan m√°s en la educaci√≥n"', 'Rosa Vargas es madre de dos estudiantes en Oakland Charter Academy. Comparte sus experiencias con las escuelas charter.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'voces_de_los_padres_las_escuelas_charter_se_enfocan_mas_en_la_educacion', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:52', '2016-01-13 04:19:52', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/voces_de_los_padres_las_escuelas_charter_se_enfocan_mas_en_la_educacion/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(156, 2, '2012-09-25 17:55:44', '2012-09-25 17:55:44', '<p>With the TripleBoost Account, parents of children ages 10-18 receive $3 for every $1 saved for their child\'s education. Parents save $500 and receive $1,500 in match money for a total of $2,000 to invest in their child\'s education. Funds can be used for:\n- College or vocational training\n- Tutoring\n- Summer enrichment camps or after-school programs\n- Music, art, or dance classes\n- A computer,\n- And more!\n<a href="http://www.earn.org/financial_services/info/tripleboost_quiz?/tripleboost">Find out if you\'re eligible!</a></p>\n\n<div class="video-container"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/aKDlQ5tG5zo?list=PL7426FA758285900D&amp;hl=en_US" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n\n<p><br>\n<br></p>\n\n<h3>About EARN</h3>\n\n<p>Everyone dreams of a better future for their family. For low-wage families, those dreams may be about going to college, buying a first home, starting a business, or having savings to fall back on during tough times.\nBut for millions of Americans, those dreams can seem unreachable. That\'s where EARN comes in. EARN is a nonprofit that gives low-income working families the power to create prosperity for generations. <a href="http://www.earn.org">Learn more.</a></p>\n', 'Parents can receive $3 for every $1 saved for their children\'s education', 'Find out if you\'re eligible and sign up today!\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'parent_can_receive_3_for_every_1_saved_for_their_childrens_education', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:52', '2016-01-13 04:19:52', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/parent_can_receive_3_for_every_1_saved_for_their_childrens_education/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(157, 2, '2012-09-25 18:03:36', '2012-09-25 18:03:36', '<p>Con la Cuenta TripleBoost de EARN, usted recibe $3 por cada $1 que usted ahorre para la educaci√≥n de su hijo. Puede ahorrar hasta $500 y recibir $1,500 en fondos que da EARN, d√°ndole un total de $2,000 para invertir en la educaci√≥n de su hijo.\nSu hijo debe estar entre las edades de 10 a 18 a√±os en el momento que usted abra una cuenta.\n- <a href="http://www.earn.org/espanol/espanol_sign_up/cuenta_tripleboost/">¬°Conteste 8 preguntas f√°ciles para ver si usted es elegible para abrir una Cuenta TripleBoost!</a></p>\n\n<div class="video-container"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/4kTCOXVuEio?list=PL7426FA758285900D&amp;hl=en_US" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n\n<h3>Sobre EARN</h3>\n\n<p>EARN es una organizaci√≥n, reconocida y premiada, sin √°nimo de lucro, con base en California que proporciona a los trabajadores de bajos ingresos el poder de crear prosperidad econ√≥mica para sus familias y para sus futuras generaciones.</p>\n', 'Usted puede recibir $3 por cada $1 que usted ahorre para la educaci√≥n de su hijo', '¬°Conteste 8 preguntas f√°ciles para ver si usted es elegible para abrir una Cuenta TripleBoost!\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'usted_puede_recibir_3_por_cada_1_que_usted_ahorre_para_la_educacion_de_su_hijo', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:52', '2016-01-13 04:19:52', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/usted_puede_recibir_3_por_cada_1_que_usted_ahorre_para_la_educacion_de_su_hijo/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(158, 2, '2012-10-01 18:08:39', '2012-10-01 18:08:39', '<p>Before you vote on November 6, you have the opportunity to get more information about local candidates running for school board in the Natomas Unified and San Juan Unified School Districts. With so much attention paid to the Presidential Election, it can be hard to get quality information about local races, but Families That Can is here to help. Come to a local voter forum and hear directly from candidates. Learn their views on education and take the opportunity to ask them questions. Cast your ballot with confidence, knowing you made an informed decision.</p>\n\n<h2>Upcoming Candidate Forums</h2>\n\n<h3>Natomas Unified</h3>\n\n<h4>Oct.3</h4>\n\n<p>6 - 8 p.m.\nHosted by the Natomas Community Association\nNatomas High School library\n3301 Fong Ranch Road, Sacramento, CA</p>\n\n<h4>Oct 17</h4>\n\n<p>6:30 - 8pm\nHosted by NP3 students\nNatomas Pacific Pathways Preparatory High School Library\n3700 Del Paso Rd | Sacramento, CA 95834</p>\n\n<h4>Oct.22</h4>\n\n<p>6 - 7:30 p.m.\nHosted by Natomas Charter School students\nBenvenuti Performing Arts Center\n4600 Blackrock Drive| Sacramento, CA</p>\n\n<h3>San Juan Unified</h3>\n\n<h4>Oct. 16</h4>\n\n<p>7 - 8:30 p.m.\nHosted by Families That Can\nCalifornia Montessori Project-Carmichael\n5330 A Gibbons Drive | Carmichael, CA 95608</p>\n\n<h2>Don\'t forget to check out our voter guides!</h2>\n\n<p>Families That Can put together <a href="/2012/09/non-partisan-voter-guides-for-november-6-2012-school-board-elections.html">these non-partisan voter guides for you to learn more about the candidates.</a></p>\n', 'Meet the Sacramento Area School Board Candidates this October', 'Before you vote on November 6, learn more about candidates running for school board in the Natomas Unified and San Juan Unified School Districts. Join us!\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'meet_the_sacramento_school_board_candidates_this_october', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:51', '2016-01-13 04:19:51', '', 