(271, 7, '2014-05-16 14:30:15', '2014-05-16 14:30:15', '<p>Approximately 350 people turned out for the <strong>CCSA Families LAUSD Board District Candidate Forum</strong>, held on Wednesday evening at Los Angeles\' Mt. Moriah Baptist Church. The forum featured four candidates vying for the Los Angeles Unified School District, Board District 1 seat. Speaking to Los Angeles-area charter school leaders, parents, teachers and others, the candidates addressed a number of issues affecting the charter school community, including support for LAUSD Superintendent John Deasy, support for the expansion of charter schools, and facilities and funding equity for charter schools.\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.816780378350372.1073741838.276454839049598&amp;type=3"><strong>See pictures of the Candidate Forum.</strong></a>\nWatch the entire Candidate Forum now!</p>\n\n<div class="video-container"><iframe width="450" height="253" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/TkPMH9aoMlg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n\n<p>The special election will coincide with the June 3 Statewide Primary Election, which is rapidly approaching. A lot is at stake in this election for our charter schools at both the state and local levels. A run-off will ensue if no one candidate captures 50%+1 of the vote. Visit the website of our sister organization, CCSA Advocates, to learn more about election issues and candidates\' positions.\nCandidates who attended included:\n- Genethia Hudley-Hayes\n- Alex Johnson\n- Rachel Johnson\n- George McKenna\nOmarosa Manigault was unable to attend due to illness, and Sherlett Hendy-Newbill and Hattie McFrazier were invited but did not attend.\n<strong>News coverage of the Candidate Forum</strong>\n- <a href="http://laschoolreport.com/mckenna-leading-school-board-race-john-deasy-lausd/">McKenna, leading in school board race, won\'t commit on Deasy</a>\n- <a href="http://laschoolreport.com/lausd-candidates-agree-on-value-of-public-charter-schools/">LAUSD candidates agree (!) on value of public charter schools</a></p>\n', 'Large Turnout for LAUSD BD 1 Candidate Forum', 'Hundreds of parents packed a South L.A. church to meet the candidates running for the LAUSD board district 1 seat, in an important special election being held June 3rd.\n', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'lausd_board_district_1_candidate_forum_-_may_14_2014', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:12', '2016-01-13 04:22:12', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/lausd_board_district_1_candidate_forum_-_may_14_2014/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(272, 7, '2014-04-16 13:34:17', '2014-04-16 13:34:17', '<h3>Reserve la fecha! Mi√©rcoles, 14 de mayo 2014</h3>\n\n<p>Siete miembros de la Junta Directiva Escolar del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los √Ångeles toman decisiones cada d√≠a sobre el futuro de su hijo. Y en este momento, la mayor√≠a de estos miembros de la Junta escolar se enfocan m√°s en mantener escuelas excelentes fuera del alcance de nuestros hijos que en asegurar que todos nuestros ni√±os reciban una educaci√≥n excelente.\nEste mes de junio hay una elecci√≥n para la Junta Escolar del Distrito 1 que podr√≠a cambiar la din√°mica de la Junta a favor de los ni√±os y las escuelas, y no a los intereses especiales.\n¬øPuede usted participar con nosotros en un <a href="http://ccsa.nationbuilder.com/bd1forum_esp">Foro de Candidatos</a>, el mi√©rcoles 14 de mayo, para conocer a cinco de los candidatos confirmados y escuchar sus respuestas a las preguntas de nuestra comunidad acerca de su apoyo de excelentes escuelas p√∫blicas ch√°rter?\n¬øCu√°l candidato luchar√° m√°s a favor de  escuelas excelentes en cada c√≥digo postal? ¬øCu√°l candidato va a representar a los ni√±os y los padres, no lo mismo de siempre? ¬øCu√°l candidato apoyar√° maestros  excelentes en las escuelas p√∫blicas ch√°rter y las escuelas p√∫blicas tradicionales por igual?\nTodo depende de nosotros. √önase a nuestro Foro el 14 de mayo.\n<a href="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/LAUSD%20BD%201%20Candidate%20Forum%20Flyer%20%28Spanish%29.pdf">Descargue el folleto para el evento.</a>\n<a href="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/LAUSD_BD1_Brochure_SPA_Web_FNL.pdf">Descargue el folleto con las declaraciones de los candidatos.</a>\n<strong>Evento</strong>\nForo de Candidatos para representar el Distrito 1 en la Junta Directiva del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los √Ångeles\nCandidatos confirmados:\n- Genethia Hudley Hayes\n- Alex Martin Johnson\n- Rachel C. Johnson\n- Omarosa O. Manigault\n- George J. McKenna, III\n<strong>Fecha</strong>\nMi√©rcoles14 de Mayo del