(294, 8, '2014-07-15 10:18:28', '2014-07-15 10:18:28', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="McKenna_and_Alex_Johnson_BD1.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/McKenna_and_Alex_Johnson_BD1.png" width="385" height="294" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nCharter school parents are focused on an important election next month that could reshape the Los Angeles Unified school board. Two candidates - education advisor <a href="http://alexjohnsonforlaschoolboard.com/">Alex Johnson</a> and former principal <a href="http://www.electmckenna.com/">George McKenna</a> - are vying for the seat in Board District 1, an area that has been chronically under-served and under-performing.\nCharter schools in the area, however, have yielded impressive gains for Latino and African American students, so parents want to make sure the candidate who wins is a strong supporter of charter schools.\nIf you\'re a voter in BD1, make sure you\'re <a href="http://registertovote.ca.gov//">registered to vote</a>. You have until July 28 to register.\n<a href="http://www.ccsaadvocates.org/">Visit CCSA Advocates to find out which candidate our sister organization has endorsed</a>.</p>\n', 'Parents Target L.A. School Board Race', 'Will the winner be a supporter of charter schools?\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'parents_target_la_school_board_race', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/parents_target_la_school_board_race/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(295, 8, '2014-07-15 10:21:21', '2014-07-15 10:21:21', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Ren_Arts_students.png (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/07/Ren_Arts_students-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nIf you think a great arts program can\'t deliver outstanding academic results, think again. Besides providing an exceptional arts program to students who are mostly low-income and have no prior experience in the arts, <a href="http://www.renarts.org/">Renaissance Arts Academy in Los Angeles</a> also boasts a 100% graduation rate. This year, the College Board took notice, selecting RenArts for their <a href="https://artsaward.collegeboard.org/past-winners.php?ep_mid=10936551&amp;ep_rid=38975792">2014 Award for Excellence and Innovation in the Arts</a>. Way to go!</p>\n', 'And the Winner Is...', 'L.A. charter school receives national honor for its arts program.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'and_the_winner_is', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/and_the_winner_is/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(296, 8, '2014-07-15 10:22:53', '2014-07-15 10:22:53', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/video/10313059-students-rising-above-carlene-ervin/#.U7GYqFA-F7I.twitter"><img alt="Aspire_grad_foster_youth_valedictorian.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/Aspire_grad_foster_youth_valedictorian.png" width="528" height="330" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nEnjoy these three stories of \'14 California charter school graduates whose inspirational achievements earned them some impressive media coverage!\nCBS got to know Carlene Ervin, a foster student at San Francisco\'s Aspire College Prep who graduated first in her class and <a href="http://sanfrancisco.cbslocal.com/video/10313059-students-rising-above-carlene-ervin/#.U7GYqFA-F7I.twitter">is now headed to Yale</a>. NBC profiled Kelly Chambers, a student at Classical Academy High School in San Diego who <a href="http://www.nbcsandiego.com/video/#!/on-air/as-seen-on/Inspirational-Student-Kelly-Chambers/261164511">spends her summers traveling to undeveloped countries</a> to provide medical care and education.\nAnd the L.A. Daily News has a great piece on Granada Hills Charter High School grad Ashley Cunningham, a chef who\'s already <a href="http://www.dailynews.com/social-affairs/20140706/granada-hills-charter-grad-cooks-her-way-to-college">climbing the professional ladder and competing nationally</a>.\nBravo to these outstanding students and the teachers, principals and charter school communities that supported them along the way!</p>\n', 'Charter Grads Make Headlines', 'A chef, a valedictorian foster student and a global medical volunteer.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'charter_grads_make_headlines', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/charter_grads_make_headlines/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(297, 8, '2014-07-15 10:25:27', '2014-07-15 10:25:27', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BG775rz1HJ4"><img alt="Redwood_City_parents_celebrate_new_charters.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/Redwood%20parents%20celebrate.png" width="491" height="323" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure> Last month, after two years of working to bring new charter school options to their community, parents celebrated the approval of two new charter schools by the Redwood City School Board. The school board unanimously voted to allow Rocketship Education and KIPP Bay Area Schools to establish new charter schools, which together expect to enroll 1,500 students. It\'s the latest example of parent power fueling the charter school movement. The parents in Redwood City are part of Innovate Public Schools, a school reform organization focused on making sure that low-income students and children of color in the greater Silicon Valley region receive an excellent education that will prepare them for success in life. Learn more at &#91;www.innovateschools.org&#93;(http://www.innovateschools.org). &#91;Watch this touching video of parents realizing that their hard work has finally paid off&#93;(https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BG775rz1HJ4).</p>\n', 'Parents Celebrate Two New Charters', 'A two-year journey brings great schools to Redwood City.\r\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'parents_celebrate_two_new_charters', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/parents_celebrate_two_new_charters/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(298, 8, '2014-07-15 12:18:43', '2014-07-15 12:18:43', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BG775rz1HJ4"><img alt="Redwood_City_parents_celebrate_new_charters.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/Redwood%20parents%20celebrate.png" width="491" height="323" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nEl mes pasado, despu√©s de dos a√±os de trabajo en traer nuevas opciones de escuelas ch√°rter a su comunidad, los padres celebraron la aprobaci√≥n de dos nuevas escuelas ch√°rter por el comit√© de escuelas de Redwood City.  El comit√© vot√≥ por unanimidad dejar "Rocketship Education" y "KIPP Bay Area Schools" a establecer dos nuevas escuelas ch√°rter, que juntas esperan inscribir a 1.500 estudiantes.  Es el ejemplo m√°s reciente del poder de los padres en alimentar el movimiento de las escuelas ch√°rter.\n<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BG775rz1HJ4">Mire este video conmovedor de los padres d√°ndose cuenta de que su trabajo arduo se ha visto recompensado</a>.</p>\n', 'Los padres celebran dos nuevas escuelas ch√°rter', 'Un viaje de dos a√±os trae escuelas geniales a Redwood.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'los_padres_celebran_dos_nuevas_escuelas_charter', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '2016-01-13 04:24:40', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/los_padres_celebran_dos_nuevas_escuelas_charter/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
