(307, 8, '2014-08-19 15:07:55', '2014-08-19 15:07:55', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Yannell_Selman.JPG (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/08/Yannell Selman-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nYannell Selman se junt√≥ con California Charter Schools Association en junio de 2014 como Organizador de Padres para las cinco escuelas ch√°rter en el distrito de Richmond.  Ella est√° orgullosa de que las escuelas con que trabaja - cada una sirviendo m√°s que nada a los estudiantes de bajos recursos - est√°n consiguiendo mejores resultados que escuelas tradicionales.\nEn esta importante posici√≥n de apoyo para las escuelas ch√°rter,  Yannell est√° construyendo un equipo de padres informados, activos y fortalecidos con respecto de los temas educativos que afectan a los estudiantes.\nSu pasi√≥n para la organizaci√≥n comunitaria empez√≥ cuando ense√±√≥ una clase del segundo grado en una escuela p√∫blica de Richmond.  Trabaj√≥ duro para prepararles a sus estudiantes para la escuela,  pero lleg√≥ a sentirse frustrada al verlos seguir a clases con profesores a quienes no les importaba el futuro de sus estudiantes.  Yannell se desanim√≥ al aprender que los padres vieron este tipo de comportamiento de profesor como algo normal en la educaci√≥n p√∫blica.\nDespu√©s de ver el √©xito de tantos de sus estudiantes que cambiaron de las tradicionales escuelas p√∫blicas a las de ch√°rter, Yannell decidi√≥ juntarse al movimiento de las escuelas ch√°rter.  Le encanta fortalecer a los padres a tomar acci√≥n y asegurar que sus hijos tengan una opci√≥n en las escuelas a que asisten y que reciban una educaci√≥n de calidad de los profesores a los cuales s√≠ les importa.\nAntes de su trabajo como profesora, Yannell particip√≥ en el trabajo de organizaci√≥n en pa√≠ses como Bolivia, Honduras y Chile como parte de su cursado universitario en Northwestern University. Cuando no est√° trabajando le gusta hacer ejercicio.  Ha participado en media maratones y tambi√©n practica cross-fit y el levantamiento de pesas.  Yannell tambi√©n es certificada en el buceo y le gusta jugar ajedrez.</p>\n', 'Conozca a nuestro equipo: Yannell Selman', 'Un ex profesor biling√ºe, Yannell trabaja con los padres en cinco escuelas ch√°rter en Richmond.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'conozca_a_nuestro_equipo_yannell_selman', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/conozca_a_nuestro_equipo_yannell_selman/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(308, 8, '2014-08-19 15:19:08', '2014-08-19 15:19:08', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Parents_at_Luskin_in_LA.jpg (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/08/Parents at Luskin in LA-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nLas familias de las escuelas ch√°rter de Los √Ångeles aportaron energ√≠a y compromiso tremendos a las elecciones especiales de ayer de la Junta Escolar del Distrito 1.  Durante los √∫ltimos meses los padres participaron en un foro de los candidatos y muchas actividades de sacar el voto que aumentaron conciencia - no solo con respecto de la carrera sino tambi√©n de la necesidad de que la Junta Escolar de LAUSD apoye escuelas ch√°rter de alta calidad.\nEn la carrera, Dr. George McKenna - quien gan√≥ con 53% del voto - y Alex Johnson expresaron apoyo para las escuelas p√∫blicas, ambos ch√°rter y tradicional,  que mejoran el rendimiento estudiantil.\nEsta elecci√≥n vio un nuevo nivel de pasi√≥n de las familias de las escuelas ch√°rter dentro del Distrito 1 y m√°s all√° tambi√©n.  Las familias de las escuelas ch√°rter van a seguir apoyando la expansi√≥n de las escuelas ch√°rter de alta calidad  y la opci√≥n educativa para servir a estudiantes en todos los c√≥digos postales.\n¬°Gracias por ser parte de la elecci√≥n y en recordar a todos que las voces de las familias de las escuelas ch√°rter importan!</p>\n', 'Familias ch√°rter energizan la carrera para la Junta Escolar de L.A.', 'En las elecciones de la Junta Escolar del Distrito 1 de LAUSD se vio un nuevo nivel de pasi√≥n y dedicaci√≥n de los padres de las escuelas ch√°rter.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'familias_charter_energizan_la_carrera_para_la_junta_escolar_de_la', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/familias_charter_energizan_la_carrera_para_la_junta_escolar_de_la/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(309, 8, '2014-09-12 12:20:27', '2014-09-12 12:20:27', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Thrive_San_Diego_Opening_Video.png (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/09/Screen Shot 2014-09-15 at 11.03.05 AM-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nThrive Public Schools opened this year after an 18-month journey for its charter petition\'s approval. The K-8 school will offer an educational experience that integrates technology through Project Based Learning, targeted instruction, homeschooling, and tinkering to meet individual student needs. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GCtFNaUWAf4&amp;list=UUuatukE6VTyzMqKIaJDGXlg&amp;mkt_tok=3RkMMJWWfF9wsRoluK7OZKXonjHpfsX56esvUa60lMI%2F0ER3fOvrPUfGjI4CTcRqI%2BSLDwEYGJlv6SgFTrfMMaNvzbgIXxI%3D">Watch the video and learn more!</a>\nAlbert Einstein Academies\' new middle school kicked off its first school year with a bang. Einstein\'s mission is to nurture, cultivate and inspire multilingual, critical thinkers who are well-rounded, responsible, global citizens uniquely prepared to thrive, lead and create positive change in the 21st century. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Llkcs8kd4xA&amp;list=UUuatukE6VTyzMqKIaJDGXlg&amp;mkt_tok=3RkMMJWWfF9wsRoluK7OZKXonjHpfsX56esvUa60lMI%2F0ER3fOvrPUfGjI4CTcRqI%2BSLDwEYGJlv6SgFTrfMMaNvzbgIXxI%3D">Watch the video and get a taste of this exciting new school. </a></p>\n', 'Meet Two of San Diego\'s Most Exciting New Schools', 'Thrive and Einstein are two powerful new additions to the San Diego charter school community.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'meet_one_of_san_diegos_most_exciting_new_schools', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/meet_one_of_san_diegos_most_exciting_new_schools/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(310, 8, '2014-09-12 12:27:21', '2014-09-12 12:27:21', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/one-movement-many-voices-video-contest.html?utm_source=ommv&amp;utm_medium=go"><img alt="Enter_Video_Contest.png (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/09/OMMV-textonly-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nCCSA wants you to submit an original and creative video for the One Movement. Many Voices. (OMMV) Video Contest! Send us your story about how a charter school has impacted you and your family. You could win a cash prize for yourself and your school. <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/one-movement-many-voices-video-contest.html?utm_source=ommv&amp;utm_medium=go&amp;mkt_tok=3RkMMJWWfF9wsRoluK7OZKXonjHpfsX56esvUa60lMI%2F0ER3fOvrPUfGjI4CTcRqI%2BSLDwEYGJlv6SgFTrfMMaNvzbgIXxI%3D">Get all the info so you can enter!</a></p>\n', 'Enter CCSA\'s Video Contest', 'Share your story of how a California charter school has positively impacted you.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'enter_ccsas_video_contest', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/enter_ccsas_video_contest/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(311, 8, '2014-09-12 13:05:21', '2014-09-12 13:05:21', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/advocacy/accountability/portraitofthemovement/?utm_source=portraitofthemovement&amp;utm_medium=go"><img alt="Portrait_of_a_Movement_2014.png (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/09/POM-2014-med-top-1-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nCCSA\'s fourth annual "Portrait of the Movement" tells the story of the large and diverse California charter schools movement now serving a half million public school students and growing every year while making significant improvements in academic performance. <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/blog/2014/08/ccsa-issues-report-showing-charters-making-significant-academic-gains.html?mkt_tok=3RkMMJWWfF9wsRoluK7OZKXonjHpfsX56esvUa60lMI%2F0ER3fOvrPUfGjI4CTcRqI%2BSLDwEYGJlv6SgFTrfMMaNvzbgIXxI%3D">Take a look.</a></p>\n', '"Portrait of the Movement" Shows Charters Making Gains', 'Tens of thousands of students are being educated in better performing charter schools than just five years ago.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'portrait_of_the_movement_shows_charters_making_gains', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/portrait_of_the_movement_shows_charters_making_gains/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(312, 8, '2014-09-15 10:35:27', '2014-09-15 10:35:27', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/advocacy/accountability/portraitofthemovement/?utm_source=portraitofthemovement&amp;utm_medium=go"><img alt="Portrait_of_a_Movement_2014.png (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/09/POM-2014-med-top-1-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nEl cuarto anual "Retrato del movimiento" de CCSA cuenta la historia del grande y diverso movimiento de las escuelas ch√°rter de California que ahora sirve a medio mill√≥n de estudiantes de escuelas p√∫blicas.  Cada a√±o crece m√°s mientras hace mejoras significativas en el rendimiento acad√©mico.  <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/advocacy/accountability/portraitofthemovement/?utm_source=portraitofthemovement&amp;utm_medium=go">Eche un vistazo.</a></p>\n', '"Retrato del movimiento"  muestra que las escuelas ch√°rter est√°n haciendo progreso', 'Decenas de miles de estudiantes est√°n recibiendo educaci√≥n en escuelas ch√°rter que son mejores que las de hace solo cinco a√±os.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'retrato_del_movimiento_muestra_que_las_escuelas_charter_estan_haciendo_progreso', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/retrato_del_movimiento_muestra_que_las_escuelas_charter_estan_haciendo_progreso/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(313, 8, '2014-09-15 10:37:14', '2014-09-15 10:37:14', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/one-movement-many-voices-video-contest.html?utm_source=ommv&amp;utm_medium=go"><img alt="Enter_Video_Contest.png (Homepage Feature: Large)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/09/OMMV-textonly-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_featured_primary.jpg" width="410" height="304" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></a></figure>\nCCSA quiere que usted entregue un video original y creativo para el concurso de "Un movimiento.  Muchas voces." ("OMMV: One movement.  Many voices.")  Env√≠enos su historia de c√≥mo una escuela ch√°rter le ha impactado a usted y su familia.  Puede ser que gane un premio de efectivo para usted y su escuela tambi√©n.  <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/blog/2014/09/one-movement-many-voices-video-contest---spread-the-word.html">Consiga toda la informaci√≥n para que se pueda entrar en el concurso.  </a></p>\n', 'Entre en el concurso de video de CCSA', 'Comparta su historia de c√≥mo una escuela ch√°rter de California le ha impactado positivamente.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'entre_en_el_concurso_de_video_de_ccsa', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/entre_en_el_concurso_de_video_de_ccsa/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(314, 8, '2014-09-15 10:39:03', '2014-09-15 10:39:03', '<p>Las escuelas p√∫blicas de Thrive abrieron despu√©s de esperar 18 meses para la aprobaci√≥n de su solicitud de ch√°rter.  La escuela primaria (k-8) va a ofrecer una experiencia p√∫blica que integra la tecnolog√≠a a trav√©s del Aprendizaje Basado en los Proyectos, la instrucci√≥n de propuestas espec√≠ficas, la educaci√≥n en el hogar, y la modificaci√≥n constante para cumplir con las necesidades individuales de los estudiantes.  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GCtFNaUWAf4">¬°Mire el video y aprenda m√°s! </a>\nLa nueva escuela de La Academia de Albert Einstein inaugur√≥ su primer a√±o escolar con un gran √©xito.  La misi√≥n de Einstein es apoyar, cultivar e inspirar a pensadores cr√≠ticos y multiling√ºes que son ciudadanos completos, responsables y globales.  Ser√°n estudiantes √∫nicamente preparados en prosperar, dirigir y crear cambio positivo en el siglo 21.  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Llkcs8kd4xA">Mire el video y aprenda de esta emocionante escuela nueva.  </a></p>\n', 'Conozca a dos de la nuevas escuelas m√°s interesantes de San Diego', 'Thrive y Einstein son dos adiciones poderosas a la comunidad de escuelas ch√°rter de San Diego.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'conozca_a_dos_de_la_nuevas_escuelas_mas_interesantes_de_san_diego', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/conozca_a_dos_de_la_nuevas_escuelas_mas_interesantes_de_san_diego/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(315, 8, '2014-10-17 13:59:05', '2014-10-17 13:59:05', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="West_Contra_Costa_parents.jpeg (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/10/West_Contra_Costa_parents-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nA month after the school year began, Maria was deeply frustrated that Lincoln Elementary - a traditional district school in West Contra Costa - still hadn\'t found a teacher for her son Javier\'s bilingual class. The substitute teacher, who was not a bilingual instructor, wasn\'t cutting it. Maria turned to Yannell Selman, a parent organizer for CCSA Families, for help finding a charter school for her son.\nBut Yannell decided to help Maria address the issue at her school. Maria gathered a dozen mothers in her home and, working with Yannell, they decided to raise the issue together at the next school board meeting. They spent a few days preparing to make their case. On the day of the meeting, more than 15 families, including several children, plus two teachers, called on the board to find a permanent, credentialed teacher for the third grade class. By the end of the meeting, the district staff were practically tripping over themselves to help the families.\nThe very next day, 45 families gathered at the school ready to hear the district\'s plan. Amazingly, the district had found a full-time teacher less than 24 hours after the families had demanded action from the board. The Richmond Confidential, the local newspaper, <a href="http://richmondconfidential.org/2014/09/26/after-five-weeks-of-substitutes-3rd-graders-at-lincoln-elementary-school-finally-have-a-permanent-teacher/">wrote an amazing story about the parent victory</a>.\nNow, these Lincoln moms are ready to continue advocating for better schools. They have formed a strong team; they know change is possible and they are ready to make it happen in West Contra Costa.</p>\n', 'West Contra Costa Parents Demand Better - and Get It!', 'When parents at a traditional school needed advocacy help, they turned to CCSA Families. The rest, as they say, is history.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'west_contra_costa_parents_demand_better_-_and_get_it', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '2016-01-13 04:24:39', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/west_contra_costa_parents_demand_better_-_and_get_it/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(316, 8, '2014-10-17 14:03:56', '2014-10-17 14:03:56', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Abby Cole &amp; Barbara Ames.JPG (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/10/Abby Cole &amp; Barbara Ames-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\n"For the first time in my life, I feel I can make a truly educated vote for school board members!" That\'s what Abby Cole, a charter school parent, said after a forum for the five candidates running for the San Juan Unified School District school board.\nCole and parents from 10 charter schools attended a public forum earlier this month organized by parents at Golden Valley Charter School and CCSA Families organizer Joanne Ahola.  The idea is to ensure that community members are following the November 4th school board election. Cole says she has already learned a lot about the candidates\' opinions on key education issues, including if and how they\'ll support high-performing charter schools.\nAre you following your local school board race? Charter schools have a lot to gain or lose in races across the state. Please vote on November 4th. Find out where the candidates in your area stand on charter school issues by <a href="http://www.ccsaadvocates.org/">visiting our sister organization, CCSA Advocates.</a></p>\n', 'San Juan Parents Organize School Board Candidate Forum', '"For the first time in my life, I feel I can make a truly educated vote for school board members!"-Abby Cole, charter school parent\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'san_juan_parents_organize_school_board_candidate_forum', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/san_juan_parents_organize_school_board_candidate_forum/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(317, 8, '2014-10-17 14:05:21', '2014-10-17 14:05:21', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Camino_Nuevo_parents.jpeg (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2014/10/Camino_Nuevo_parents-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nThey started lining up the night before the school board meeting. Parents at some of L.A.\'s leading charter schools assembled on the sidewalk outside the district\'s downtown headquarters. Knowing the next day\'s board meeting would be packed, they went the extra mile by camping out all night to make sure they would make it into the meeting to show their support for their schools.\nThe next day, October 14, 2014, the school board voted on whether to renew charters run by Alliance, Aspire, Camino Nuevo, Crown Prep and New Village. More than 300 parents, clad in colorful school t-shirts, packed the board room, waiting to make their case to the board.\nThey didn\'t have to say a word. Their presence said it all. The board voted to approve all seven schools. Parents cheered, hugged, high-fived and then went back to their families, at ease knowing that their children would continue to attend the excellent schools they\'d chosen.</p>\n', 'L.A. Parents Help Charter Schools Get Renewed', 'As the L.A. school board voted on the renewal of seven charter schools, parents gathered to show their support. The board voted yes to all seven!\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'la_parents_help_charter_schools_get_renewed', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/la_parents_help_charter_schools_get_renewed/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(318, 8, '2014-10-17 14:06:34', '2014-10-17 14:06:34', '<p>For the first time, thanks in part to your advocacy, a law sponsored by the California Charter Schools Association was passed by the Assembly and the Senate and signed by the governor. AB 948 will enable more charter schools, particularly those serving low-income students, to secure safe, reliable facilities.\nThe governor also vetoed two bills, SB 1263 and AB 913, that would have crippled the independence of charter schools.\nThank you to the hundreds of charter school families who sent emails, letters and faxes in support of the charter school movement. Our collective advocacy helped make this legislative session a huge success!</p>\n', 'You Made a Difference in State Charter School Law', 'Families across California helped make this the most successful legislative session in recent history for charter schools.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'you_made_a_difference_in_state_charter_school_law', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '2016-01-13 04:24:38', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/you_made_a_difference_in_state_charter_school_law/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
