(330, 9, '2014-11-25 15:14:14', '2014-11-25 15:14:14', '<p><img src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/photo-families-alliance-baxter-opening.png" align="right">Observe las caras sonrientes de las familias y los maestros mientras dan la bienvenida a una nueva preparatoria ch√°rter, la Alliance Alice M. Baxter College-Ready High School, a San Pedro en L.A. Es una de las 87 nuevas escuelas que abrieron este a√±o en California, elevando el n√∫mero total de las escuelas ch√°rter del estado a 1.184.\nEl movimiento est√° creciendo, lo cual es evidencia que las familias quieren m√°s y mejores opciones de educaci√≥n.  ¬°Y usted es parte del movimiento!</p>\n', 'Los Padres de L.A. Dan la Bienvenida a Alliance Charter High School', 'Es una de las 87 nuevas escuelas ch√°rter que abrieron este a√±o a lo largo de California\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'los_padres_de_la_dan_la_bienvenida_a_alliance_charter_high_school', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:37', '2016-01-13 04:24:37', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/los_padres_de_la_dan_la_bienvenida_a_alliance_charter_high_school/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(331, 8, '2015-01-15 12:58:47', '2015-01-15 12:58:47', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="icon-rock-the-vote-wide.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/icon-rock-the-vote-wide.png" width="210" height="140" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nFamilies across Los Angeles are watching closely as four school board races get underway. The school board has the power to approve or deny charter schools, so there\'s a lot at stake for the thousands of parents whose children attend more than 285 charter schools in L.A. Unified. The election is coming up fast on March 3rd.\nDo you know who you\'re voting for? <a href="http://www.ccsaadvocates.org/">Visit CCSA Advocates</a> to learn where the candidates stand on our schools and how you can get involved. There are also several forums where the candidates will debate the most urgent issues affecting our schools. Please consider <a href="http://www.unitedwayla.org/2015-candidate-forum-series/">attending a forum in your board district.</a>\nAnd if you\'re not registered to vote, take two minutes and <a href="http://ccsafamilies.org/register-to-vote.html">register online</a>. It\'s easy.</p>\n', 'All Eyes on L.A. School Board Election', 'Four races will have a major impact on charter schools.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'all_eyes_on_la_school_board_election', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:37', '2016-01-13 04:24:37', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/all_eyes_on_la_school_board_election/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(332, 8, '2015-01-15 13:17:44', '2015-01-15 13:17:44', '<p>Dirty streets are a fact of life in some neighborhoods. But the situation around one particular charter school campus in South Los Angeles was out of hand. The corner of Adams and 26th Street - where two Green Dot schools share a campus - had long been used as an illegal dumping ground by trucking and waste companies. It got so bad that a few months back, a broken boat was left sitting on the corner. Parents worried their children weren\'t safe walking to and from school. The schools were doing as much as they could to keep the area clean, but the city wasn\'t responsive to their requests for help.\nSo what did parents do? They took matters into their own hands. With the help of CCSA Families organizer Diana Marin Isaac, parents gathered 400 signatures on a petition that they took to the office of their City Councilmember, Curren Price, Jr. Within a few weeks, the corner was getting cleaned up regularly. It\'s still not spotless, and the nearby streets still need major attention from the city, but parents are proud that they\'ve been able to noticeably improve the situation. Stay tuned. These parents are just getting started!</p>\n', 'Parents Demand Clean-Up, Get Results', 'The city ignored them at first, but charter parents persisted.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'parents_demand_clean-up_get_results', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:36', '2016-01-13 04:24:36', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/parents_demand_clean-up_get_results/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(333, 8, '2015-01-15 13:21:42', '2015-01-15 13:21:42', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Caiber_parents_board_meeting_West_Contra_Costa.jpg (Newsletter Feature Thumbnail)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2015/01/IMG_6327-cropped-proto-custom_10.jpg" width="225" height="174" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nA school community deserves a home. But West Contra Costa Unified officials wants Caliber Beta Academy to divide its classrooms among two or three campuses - instead of a single location. So parents at the elementary school, which serves mostly Latino, African American and low-income students, are trying to change hearts and minds.\nEarlier this month, nearly 200 parents gathered at a school board meeting to ask for a permanent facility for Caliber Beta Academy. Their efforts garnered <a href="http://www.contracostatimes.com/contra-costa-times/ci_27283111/west-contra-costa-school-district-faces-tight-timeline">coverage in the local newspaper</a>. Parents have also been writing letters and meeting individually with board members to voice their concerns. In the coming weeks, district officials will make a decision. Whatever happens, these parents have proudly advocated for their kids and their charter school!</p>\n', 'Charter Families Advocate for Permanent Home', 'Parents at Caliber Beta Academy are rallying to secure a proper facility for their school.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'charter_families_advocate_for_permanent_home', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:36', '2016-01-13 04:24:36', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/charter_families_advocate_for_permanent_home/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(334, 8, '2015-01-15 13:24:24', '2015-01-15 13:24:24', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Vote_in_OMMV_video_contest.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/CCSA_HP_Image_r1%20copy.png" width="640" height="494" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\n<a href="http://www.ccsa.org/ommv-videogallery.html">Watch these touching videos</a> submitted by parents, teachers, leaders and supporters, sharing how charter schools have impacted their lives. Then <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/ommv-videogallery.html">vote for your favorite</a> one before February 5th!\nFirst Place winner will be awarded a $5,000 cash prize along with a $10,000 donation to the California charter school of their choice. Second Place winner will receive $2,000 along with a $3,000 donation to the California charter school of their choice. Third Place winner will receive $1,000 and a $2,000 donation to the California charter school of their choice.</p>\n', 'Help a Charter School Win $10k!', 'Pick your favorite in CCSA\'s "One Movement, Many Voices" video contest.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'help_a_charter_school_win_10k', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:36', '2016-01-13 04:24:36', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/help_a_charter_school_win_10k/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(335, 8, '2015-01-15 13:31:35', '2015-01-15 13:31:35', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="icon-rock-the-vote-wide.png" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/icon-rock-the-vote-wide.png" width="210" height="140" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nA lo largo de Los √Ångeles las familias est√°n mirando fijadamente mientras empiezan cuatro carreras pol√≠ticas para la junta escolar.  La junta escolar tiene el poder de aprobar o negar las escuelas ch√°rter, entonces hay muchas cosas en juego para los miles de padres que tienen hijos que asisten a m√°s de 285 escuelas ch√°rter en el Distrito Escolar Unificado de L.A.  La elecci√≥n del 3 de marzo est√° por llegar.\n¬øSabe usted por qui√©n va a votar?  <a href="http://www.ccsaadvocates.org/">Visita CCSA Advocates</a> para averiguar las posiciones de los candidatos acerca de nuestras escuelas y c√≥mo puede involucrarse.  Tambi√©n habr√° muchos foros en los cuales los candidatos debatir√°n los temas m√°s urgentes que est√°n afectando nuestras escuelas.  Por favor <a href="http://www.unitedwayla.org/2015-candidate-forum-series/">trate de asistir a un foro en su distrito escolar</a>.\nY si no se ha inscrito para votar, tome dos minutos e <a href="http://ccsafamilies.org/register-to-vote.html">inscr√≠base en l√≠nea</a>.  Es f√°cil.</p>\n', 'Todos los ojos puestos en la elecci√≥n para la Junta Escolar de L.A.', 'Cuatro carreras pol√≠ticas tendr√°n un gran impacto en las escuelas ch√°rter.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'todos_los_ojos_puestos_en_la_eleccion_para_la_junta_escolar_de_la', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:36', '2016-01-13 04:24:36', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/todos_los_ojos_puestos_en_la_eleccion_para_la_junta_escolar_de_la/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(336, 8, '2015-01-15 14:44:39', '2015-01-15 14:44:39', '<p>Las calles sucias son un hecho de la vida en algunos barrios.  Sin embargo, la situaci√≥n alrededor de una escuela ch√°rter en particular de South Los √Ångles estaba fuera  de control.  La esquina de Adams con la Calle 26 - donde dos escuelas Green Dot comparten un campus - siempre hab√≠a sido usada como un vertedero ilegal por las empresas de carga pesada y residuos.  La situaci√≥n se empeor√≥ tanto que hace unos meses una lancha descompuesta fue abandonada en la esquina.  Los padres estaban preocupados de que sus hijos no estuvieran seguros mientras caminaban hacia y desde la escuela.  Las escuelas estaban haciendo todo lo posible para mantener el √°rea limpia, pero la ciudad no respond√≠a a sus pedidos para ayuda.\n¬øEntonces qu√© hicieron los padres?  Tomaron los asuntos en sus propias manos.  Con la ayuda de Diana Marin Isaac, organizadora de Las Familias de CCSA, los padres recolectaron 400 firmas en una petici√≥n que llevaron a la oficina de Current Price Jr, miembro del concejo municipal.  Dentro de unas pocas semanas la esquina estaba recibiendo limpiezas frecuentes.  A pesar de que todav√≠a no est√° impecable y que las calles cercanas necesitan atenci√≥n significativa de la ciudad, los padres est√°n orgullosos de que han podido mejorar la situaci√≥n inmensamente.  Mant√©ngase al tanto.  ¬°Estos padres est√°n apenas empezando!</p>\n', 'Padres exigen una limpieza y reciben resultados', 'Al principio la ciudad los ignor√≥, pero los padres persistieron.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'padres_exigen_una_limpieza_y_reciben_resultados', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:36', '2016-01-13 04:24:36', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/padres_exigen_una_limpieza_y_reciben_resultados/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(337, 8, '2015-01-15 14:48:02', '2015-01-15 14:48:02', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Caiber_parents_board_meeting_West_Contra_Costa.jpg" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/IMG_6327.jpg" width="4272" height="2848" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nTodas las comunidades escolares merecen un hogar.  Sin embargo, los oficiales del Distrito Escolar Unificado de West Contra Costa quieren que Caliber Beta Academy divida sus aulas entre dos o tres campus diferentes - en vez de tenerlas en una sola ubicaci√≥n.  Entonces los padres de la escuela primaria, la cual posee en gran mayor√≠a a estudiantes latinos, afroamericanos y de familias de bajos ingresos, est√°n tratando de cambiar corazones y mentes.\nA principios de este mes, casi 200 padres se reunieron en la reuni√≥n de la junta escolar para pedir un campus permanente para Caliber Beta Academy. Sus esfuerzos obtuvieron cobertura <a href="http://www.contracostatimes.com/contra-costa-times/ci_27283111/west-contra-costa-school-district-faces-tight-timeline">en el peri√≥dico local</a>.  Los padres tambi√©n han estado escribiendo cartas y reuni√©ndose individualmente con miembros de la junta escolar para expresar sus preocupaciones.  En las semanas que vienen, oficiales del distrito tomar√°n una decisi√≥n.  Pase lo que pase, ¬°estos padres han defendido orgullosamente a sus hijos y su escuela ch√°rter!</p>\n', 'Las familias ch√°rter promueven para un campus permanente', 'Los padres de Caliber Beta Academy est√°n reuniendo fuerzas para asegurar un campus apropiado para su escuela.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'las_familias_charter_promueven_para_un_campus_permanente', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/las_familias_charter_promueven_para_un_campus_permanente/', 0, 'post', '', 0) ;
