(346, 8, '2015-02-24 16:26:06', '2015-02-24 16:26:06', '<p>Si usted es un padre en Richmond que tiene inter√©s en las escuelas ch√°rter, es una gran posibilidad que haya pasado el 7 de febrero en "El fin de semana de opciones para los padres."  El evento recibi√≥ m√°s de 500 personas, inclusive a representativos de cada una de las 11 escuelas ch√°rter de la zona.  Los asistentes aprendieron de sus opciones educativas y tambi√©n disfrutaron de una serie de presentaciones de los estudiantes.  M√°s de una docena de organizaciones de la comunidad que proveen tutor√≠a, actividades para despu√©s de la escuela y otras oportunidades de enriquecimiento tambi√©n asistieron.  Fue una oportunidad tremenda para que las familias pudieran conocer sus escuelas ch√°rter - ¬°y tambi√©n para que se conocieran unos a otros!</p>\n', 'El fin de semana de opciones para los padres recibe 500 asistentes', 'El apoyo para las escuelas ch√°rter est√° en auge en Richmond, donde los vecinos se reunieron recientemente para aprender m√°s de sus opciones educativas.\n', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'el_fin_de_semana_de_opciones_para_los_padres_recibe_500_asistentes', '', '', '2016-01-13 21:51:00', '2016-01-13 21:51:00', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/el_fin_de_semana_de_opciones_para_los_padres_recibe_500_asistentes/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(347, 8, '2015-03-31 13:19:42', '2015-03-31 13:19:42', '<p>Charter schools are improving the quality of American education in major cities. That\'s according to a <a href="http://urbancharters.stanford.edu/index.php">huge national study just released by the Center for Research on Educational Outcomes (CREDO)</a> at Stanford University. It found that many urban charter schools are providing "superior academic learning for their students, in many cases quite dramatically better." The study also found positive results for nearly all student subgroups, especially for students who are minority and in poverty. While this news isn\'t surprising to charter school parents, it\'s an exciting addition to the growing library of independent research confirming what parents already know - that charter schools are helping to deliver on the promise of a great public education. <a href="http://urbancharters.stanford.edu/index.php">Read more about the CREDO report.</a></p>\n\n<p><strong><em>https://www.ccsa.org/cgi-bin/mt/mt.cgi?__mode=view&amp;_type=asset&amp;id=4911&amp;blog_id=10</em></strong></p>\n', 'Stanford Finds Urban Charter Schools Get "Superior" Results', 'The latest research by Stanford University shows the exceptional performance of urban charter schools across the country.\r\n', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'stanford_finds_urban_charter_schools_get_superior_results', '', '', '2016-01-20 21:26:34', '2016-01-20 21:26:34', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/stanford_finds_urban_charter_schools_get_superior_results/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(348, 8, '2015-03-31 13:24:35', '2015-03-31 13:24:35', '<p>This month\'s school board election at L.A. Unified sent several candidates into a runoff. The school board has the power to approve or deny charter schools, so there\'s a lot at stake for the thousands of parents whose children attend more than 285 charter schools in L.A. Unified. The runoff election is May 19th.</p>\n\n<p>Do you know who you\'re voting for? Visit <a href="http://www.ccsaadvocates.org/">CCSA Advocates</a> to learn where the candidates stand on our schools and how you can get involved. And if you\'re not registered to vote, take two minutes and register online. It\'s easy.</p>\n\n<p>*** find an image like this or similar https://www.ccsa.org/cgi-bin/mt/mt.cgi?__mode=view&amp;_type=asset&amp;id=2544&amp;blog_id=10***</p>\n', 'L.A. Parents Get Ready for the Runoff', 'The school board race continues, and charter families are watching.\r\n', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'la_parents_get_ready_for_the_runoff', '', '', '2016-01-20 21:25:57', '2016-01-20 21:25:57', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/la_parents_get_ready_for_the_runoff/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(349, 8, '2015-03-31 13:26:28', '2015-03-31 13:26:28', '<p>Legislators in Sacramento are being pressured to pass new laws that will hinder charter school independence and effectiveness. So far, they\'ve only heard from special interests. Now they need to hear from you. Please take a minute to <a href="https://www.votervoice.net/CCSA/campaigns/39808/respond">sign this petition opposing Assembly Bill 787</a>, which would take away the independence of charter schools across California.</p>\n\n<p>Stay tuned in the coming weeks and watch for emails inviting you to share your voice, stand up for charter schools, and tell lawmakers not to create new laws that get in the way of charter school success.</p>\n\n<p><strong><em>https://www.ccsa.org/cgi-bin/mt/mt.cgi?__mode=view&amp;&#95;type=asset&amp;id=2544&amp;blog&#95;id=10</em></strong></p>\n', 'Help Fight Anti-Charter Legislation!', 'Sacramento is considering several new laws that threaten charter schools. Will you stand up for your school?\r\n', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'help_fight_anti-charter_legislation', '', '', '2016-01-20 22:27:44', '2016-01-20 22:27:44', '', 0, 'http://192.168.20.50/wp/help_fight_anti-charter_legislation/', 0, 'post', '', 0),
