(576, 1, '2015-12-31 02:57:12', '2015-12-31 02:57:12', 'The scene is becoming more common. Each month at the meeting of the school board of the Los Angeles Unified School, District make hundreds of families outside row only for the chance to tell the board how much care about their schools. That is precisely what happened to the meeting this month, parents and students in charter schools Aspire, Camino Nuevo and Green Dot met to ensure that the board voted to renew its charter schools. And that is exactly what made the meeting. L.A. Live charter families!\r\nFamilies are also spreading the word about a substantial problem facing schools of LA: the search for the next superintendent. By filling out hundreds of surveys and attending public meetings, parents and students in charter schools are ensuring that the school board know that the next superintendent must support charter schools and school choice. It is expected that the school board chooses the next superintendent for later this year', 'Families L.A. promotion flexes its muscles', 'Padres y estudiantes opinan sobre la b√∫squeda de un superintendente y ayudan a que sus escuelas ch√°rter se renueven\r\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '394-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-31 02:57:12', '2015-12-31 02:57:12', '', 394, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/394-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
