(862, 3, '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '<p>On Wednesday June 27, the Oakland Unified School District (OUSD) board is scheduled to vote to potentially put a tax measure on the November ballot which would raise $475 million for upgrades and improvements to school buildings. Right now, this facilities bond excludes charter schools - that is unacceptable!\nAt least one out of five public school students in Oakland Unified attend charter schools, but the bond, as currently drafted, doesn\'t even mention charter schools, much less guarantee them a fair share of any potential funding.\nIn addition, as taxpayers, parents would be forced to pay higher taxes, yet their own kids would not be benefitted.  The OUSD board needs to hear from parents and students like you!  Other major districts throughout California have included charters in Bonds--there\'s no reason OUSD should treat us like second class citizens!\n- <a href="http://www.votervoice.net/groups/ftc/advocacy/?issueid=29147">Send them an email today!</a>\nYou can also call the board members at (510) 879-8199.</p>\n', 'Action Alert: Tell the Oakland School Board Charter Students Deserve a Fair Share of Facilities Bond!', 'On Wednesday June 27, the Oakland Unified School District (OUSD) board is scheduled to vote to potentially put a tax measure on the November ballot which would raise $475 million for upgrades and improvements to school buildings. Right now, this facilities bond excludes charter schools - that is unacceptable!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '130-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '', 130, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/130-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(863, 3, '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '<p>La semana pasada, la Legislatura Estatal aprob√≥ el proyecto de ley principal para establecer el presupuesto estatal para el a√±o fiscal 2012-13. Para entrar en vigor, el Gobernador Brown debe firmar esa medida presupuestaria, la AB 1464.\nMIENTRAS CONDUC√çAMOS UN DETALLADO AN√ÅLISIS DE LA MEDIDA, LA CUAL ES DE 736 PAGINAS, NOS DIMOS CUENTA QUE LA LEGISLATURA NOS HIZO UNA MALA JUGADA A LAS ESCUELAS CHARTER, ELIMINANDO PARTE DE NUESTRO FINANCIAMIENTO.\nLa medida presupuestaria original inclu√≠a $50 millones de d√≥lares en subvenciones para cubrir el crecimiento de nuevos estudiantes que asisten a las escuelas ch√°rter en California. Ahora parece que la Legislatura HA SACADO ese financiamiento, lo que causar√° una reducci√≥n proporcional en las subvenciones que reciben todas las escuelas ch√°rter.\n<strong>De ser aprobada esta decisi√≥n, las escuelas p√∫blicas ch√°rter perder√≠an aproximadamente  $100 por cada estudiante.</strong>\nLa decisi√≥n de eliminar el financiamiento para estimular crecimiento en las escuelas p√∫blicas ch√°rter, la cual perjudica directamente a m√°s de 412.000 estudiantes que asisten a estas escuelas, es inaceptable, y se tom√≥ en una junta privada y con poca transparencia al p√∫blico.\nEl Gobernador tiene que tomar la decisi√≥n de aprobar o vetar el presupuesto antes del 27 de junio.\n¬°LEVANTE SU VOZ HOY MISMO!\nLlame a sus legisladores y p√≠dales que restauren las subvenciones para cubrir el crecimiento de nuevos estudiantes que asisten a las escuelas ch√°rter (Categorical Block Grant Growth Funding). <a href="http://www.leginfo.ca.gov/yourleg.html">Se puede utilizar esta herramienta para buscar a sus legisladores y sus n√∫meros telef√≥nicos.</a> Inscriba su c√≥digo postal.\nLlame a la oficina del Gobernador al 916-445-2841, para darle las gracias por su apoyo a las escuelas ch√°rter, y pedirle que vete el presupuesto.</p>\n', '¬°Llame Hoy Mismo Para Oponerse a Recortes Propuestos Contra Las Escuelas Ch√°rter!', 'En la √∫ltima versi√≥n del presupuesto estatal, las escuelas p√∫blicas ch√°rter perder√≠an aproximadamente  $100 por cada estudiante. El Gobernador tiene que tomar su decisi√≥n antes del 27 de junio. ¬°Llame a los legisladores hoy mismo!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '129-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '', 129, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/129-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(864, 3, '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '<h4>LATEST UPDATE - Thursday, June 21, 4:42 p.m.</h4>\n\n<p>Today, the Governor and Democratic leaders announced an agreement on the remaining parts of the budget.  Included in that agreement, according to a summary document on the key deal points, is growth funding for the Charter School Categorical Block Grant, and language to improve operations, increase access to facilities, and ease cash flow problems.\nWhile we haven\'t seen actual language, and may not see it until Tuesday when the Legislature is expected to vote on this agreement, it appears that the $50 million that was cut has been restored!\nYOU CAN STILL HELP - as we well know, nothing is certain until a vote has been taken, and we need to urge legislators to approve this compromise agreement with the charter school categorical funding in it.  Our detractors may try to undo this deal before it comes before the Legislature on Tuesday.  We need you to continue to call in support of this funding.\nWe need to tell our elected officials that we expect more for our kids.  <a href="http://www.votervoice.net/CCSA/Campaigns/29002/Respond">FIND OUT HOW YOU CAN MAKE A DIFFERENCE TODAY.</a></p>\n\n<h3>Background on this Issue</h3>\n\n<p>Last week, the Legislature passed the main bill outlining the state budget for the 2012-13 fiscal year. To go into effect, the Governor must sign the Budget Bill (AB 1464).\n<strong>AS WE REVIEWED THE 736-PAGE BUDGET BILL, IT BECAME CLEAR THAT THE LEGISLATURE PLAYED DIRTY TRICKS WITH CHARTER SCHOOL FUNDING.</strong>\nThe original budget proposal included $50 million in growth in the charter school categorical block grant to account for the growth in number of new students attending California\'s charter public schools. It now appears that the Legislature has REMOVED that growth funding, which will mean a proportional cut in the categorical block grant to all charter schools.\n<strong>This decision means a cut of approximately $110 per charter school student, on average.</strong>\nGovernor Jerry Brown has until Wednesday, June 27 to decide to sign or veto this budget.\nConfused how this process works? <a href="/2012/03/how-the-california-legislature-passes-the-budget.html">Learn more about the CA legislature\'s process for passing the budget.</a></p>\n', 'Urgent: Call Today to Stop Cuts to Charter Schools!', 'The latest version of the state budget would cut an average of $100 per student for charter schools. The Governor has until June 27 to decide - call legislators today to stop this cut!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '128-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '', 128, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/128-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(865, 3, '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '<p>De PACT:\nTenemos un crisis en el Condado de Santa Clara: las dos secundarias con el rendimiento acad√©mico m√°s alto en Alum Rock, la Acad√©mia Renaissance y la Acad√©mia KIPP Heartwood, tienen listas de espera llenas con cientos de familias desesperadas por entrar. Para estas familias, es un riesgo grande poner sus ni√±os en las otras secundarias de Alum Rock: solo un promedio de 50% de los estudiantes se graduan preparados para ser exitosos en la preparatoria. Estas estad√≠sticas son a√∫n m√°s sombr√≠as para los estudiantes Latinos y de bajos ingresos..\n<em>"Yo estoy aqu√≠ porque estoy cansada de o√≠r que nuestros hijos Latinos no van a llegar con √©xito a la universidad, que solo ser√°n "obreros". Estoy aqu√≠, llena de coraje y frustraci√≥n, para demostrarles que nuestros hijos Latinos son capaces de ser exitosos en la universidad y m√°s all√°. Quiero que todos los ni√±os, sin discriminar a nadie, tengan las mismas oportunidades para una educaci√≥n de calidad."</em>\n- Maria Teresa Barcenas, una de los padres lideres de PACT\nPadres demandan m√°s buenas opciones en Alum Rock. Padres de PACT creen que todos los ni√±os merecen el derecho a una educaci√≥n excelente sin importar su estatus economico u origen √©tnico.\n¬°Esperamos verlo/a all√≠!\n- <a href="http://www.telemundoareadelabahia.com/noticias/Protesta-de-PACT-156511895.html">Vea el reporte en Telemundo.</a>\nLos Comites de padres lideres de PACT en las escuelas Rocketship Si Se Puede, Rocketship Los Suenos y Goss Elementary\n¬°<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/320799091332175/">RSVP con Facebook</a> y invite a sus amigos!\nPara m√°s informaci√≥n, por favor contacte:\n- Organizador de PACT Marie Moore:  (408) 230-5239\n- Padre L√≠der Maria Teresa Barcenas: (408) 324-4962</p>\n', 'Padres de PACT en Alum Rock demandan la replicaci√≥n de buenas escuelas', 'PACT les invita a su proximo evento el 18 de Junio!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '127-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '', 127, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/127-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(866, 3, '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '<p>From PACT:\nWe have a middle school crisis across Santa Clara County. The two highest performing middle schools in Alum Rock, Renaissance Academy and KIPP Heartwood Academy, have waiting lists of hundreds of families desperate to get in. Putting their kids in the other middle schools in Alum Rock is a huge gamble for families: only an average of 50% of students graduate prepared to succeed in high school. These statistics are even bleaker for low-income and Latino students.\n<em>"I\'m here because I\'m tired of hearing that our Latino children will not be successful in college, that they will only be \'laborers\'. I\'m here, full of anger and frustration, to demonstrate that our Latino children are capable of being successful in college and beyond. I want all children, without discrimination, to have the same opportunities for a quality education."</em>\n- Maria Teresa Barcenas, PACT parent leader\nParents demand more great options in Alum Rock. PACT parents believe all children have the right to an excellent education no matter their economic status or ethnicity.\nHope to see you there!\nPACT Parent Organizing Committees\nRocketship Si Se Puede, Rocketship Los Sue√±os, and Goss Elementary School\nJoin the growing movement at PACT\'s next community action meeting:\nMonday, June 18, 6 p.m.\nMayfair Community Center\n2039 Kammerer Ave.\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/320799091332175/">RSVP on Facebook</a> and invite your friends!\nFor more information, please contact:\n- PACT Organizer Marie Moore: (408) 230-5239\n- Parent Leader Maria Teresa Barcenas: (408) 324-4962\n<em><a href="http://www.pactsj.org/">People Acting in Community Together (PACT)</a> is an inter-faith, grassroots organization that empowers everyday people to create a more just community based in San Jose.</em></p>\n', 'PACT Parents in Alum Rock Demand Replication of Great Middle Schools', 'You\'re invited to the next meeting on June 18!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '126-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '', 126, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/126-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(867, 3, '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '<p>Una entrada poca segura, una escuela sin laboratorios de ciencias, ni cafeter√≠a, ni campos de juego...La frustraci√≥n por parte de los alumnos de Watts Learning Center Middle School con la falta de calidad en las instalaciones de su escuela, que este a√±o hicieron un video para compartir con el distrito escolar y la comunidad.\nDurante los √∫ltimos meses, los l√≠deres de la escuela y padres de familia pidieron a los miembros de la Junta Directiva del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los Angeles y al Superintendente John Deasy ayuda para obtener mejores instalaciones.\nMiembros de la comunidad y pastores levantaron sus voces para apoyar a la escuela, y uno de los l√≠deres de la escuela escribi√≥ un art√≠culo en la publicaci√≥n local, L.A. Wave.\nLa escuela se enter√≥ recientemente que el pr√≥ximo a√±o tendr√°n instalaciones nuevas y mejores ubicadas dentro de una nueva escuela en la misma comunidad.\n"Estamos muy agradecidos de que el Superintendente Deasy y Richard Vladovic de la Junta Directiva han reconocido las necesidades de los estudiantes del sur de Los √Ångeles y gracias a sus esfuerzos y el apoyo de la comunidad, la escuela cuenta ahora con una instalaci√≥n completamente nueva", dijo KW Tulloss de Families That Can. "Ahora, los ni√±os en Watts tienen el espacio ideal que se merecen para aprender."\nEn febrero, el Superintendente Deasy se dirigi√≥ a m√°s de 5,000 padres de las escuelas ch√°rter de Los Angeles, prometiendo trabajar con las familias para asegurar que las escuelas ch√°rter tengan instalaciones adecuadas.\nFuturo Prep, una escuela ch√°rter que abri√≥ sus puertas hace tres a√±os en el este de Los Angeles, tambi√©n ha sufrido muchas dificultades en cuanto de sus instalaciones.\nLa mayor√≠a de las familias residen en Boyle Heights, pero las instalaciones que la escuela recibi√≥ por parte del Distrito Escolar est√°n ubicadas a m√°s de ocho kil√≥metros de distancia.\nLos padres de familia de esta escuela escribieron cartas a sus representantes en la Junta Directiva del distrito, y tambi√©n <a href="http://www.laopinion.com/article/20120319/IMPORT01/303199898">hablaron con el peri√≥dico La Opini√≥n sobre su lucha</a>.\n"Es una pena que una escuela tan buena tenga que andar rogando por un espacio para nuestros hijos," coment√≥ Marisol Chavez, una madre de Futuro Prep, al peri√≥dico.\nRecientemente, los padres se enteraron de que en el pr√≥ximo a√±o escolar, la escuela finalmente tendr√° su lugar en su comunidad de Boyle Heights.</p>\n', 'Escuelas Charter Obtienen Mejores Instalaciones Gracias a Esfuerzos de Padres de Familia', 'Levantaron sus voces y el distrito escolar respondi√≥.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '125-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '', 125, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/125-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(868, 3, '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '<div class="figure embedded-image none"><img alt="watts_learning_center_middle_school_facility.jpg (Entry/Page Lead Image)" src="/assets_c/2012/06/watts_learning_center_middle_school_facility-cropped-proto-ftc_theme___lead.jpg" width="612" height="269" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></div>\n\n<p>An unsafe entry, no science labs, no cafeteria and no playing fields...Students at Watts Learning Center Middle School were so frustrated with the poor quality of their school facilities this year that they made a video to share with the school district and the community.\nOver the past few months, the school leaders and parents reached out to the Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD) board and Superintendent John Deasy for help getting a better facility. Community members and local clergy also spoke out in support of the school and the school leader <a href="http://wavenewspapers.com/opinion/article_b40cc50a-63d8-11e1-bd1b-001a4bcf6878.html">wrote an article for the local newspaper, the LA Wave</a>.\n<strong>The school recently learned that next year, they will have a new and improved home on part of a brand new high school campus in the neighborhood!</strong>\n"We\'re very grateful that the superintendent and school board member Dr. Vladovic recognized the needs of the students of south Los Angeles and thanks to their efforts and the community support, the school now has a brand-new facility," said KW Tulloss of Families That Can. "Now the children in Watts have the great space to learn that they deserve."\nSuperintendent Deasy addressed more than 5,000 charter school parents at the "Schools We Can Believe In" rally in February, promising to work with families to ensure that charter schools have equitable facilities.\n- <a href="/2011/06/a-parents-guide-to-charter-facility-challenges.html">Learn more about the facilities challenges that charter schools face and how parents can support their schools around this issue.</a></p>\n', 'LA School Gets a Better Facility Thanks to Parents and Students Speaking Out!', 'Parents and students spoke out and the Los Angeles school board and superintendent responded to ensure that students have the safe, quality facility they deserve!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '124-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '2016-01-13 04:19:54', '', 124, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/124-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
