(969, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '<p>Did you know that you can vote by mail? In California, you can register to vote by mail for just one election or you can sign up as a Permanent Absentee Voter and always receive your ballot in the mail automatically.\nHere are 4 great reasons to vote by mail:</p>\n\n<h3>1. It\'s easy.</h3>\n\n<p>You can register as a Permanent Absentee Voter just by <a href="http://www.sos.ca.gov/elections/vote-by-mail/pdf/fill-in-vote-by-mail-app-instruct.pdf">filling out this simple form</a>.\nLos Angeles County voters should mail the completed form to:\nDean Logan, Registrar - Recorder/County Clerk\nP.O. Box 1024\nNorwalk, CA 90651-1024\nThose in other counties should send them to their respective registrar.</p>\n\n<h3>2. It\'s convenient.</h3>\n\n<p>You don\'t even have to get dressed or figure out where to go to vote. Just fill out your ballot in the comfort of your own home, at the time that is convenient for you.</p>\n\n<h3>3. Never forget an election.</h3>\n\n<p>Your voter guide and ballot will automatically arrive in the mail a couple of weeks before the election.</p>\n\n<h3>4. Life happens!</h3>\n\n<p>Don\'t let it prevent your vote from counting. By voting early, nothing can keep you from the polls - whether an emergency at work or a sick child. Don\'t worry - if you forget to mail your ballot before election day, you can always take it in to your polling place and submit it in person.\nMake sure your vote counts! Vote early! Vote by mail!</p>\n', '4 Great Reasons to Vote By Mail', 'Did you know that you can vote by mail? In California, you can register to vote by mail for just one election or you can sign up as a Permanent Absentee Voter and always receive your ballot in the mail automatically.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '227-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '', 227, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/227-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(970, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '<p>¬øSab√≠a que se puede votar por correo? En California, se puede registrar para recibir su boleta para la pr√≥xima elecci√≥n por correo o se puede registrarse como Votante Permanente por Correo para recibir sus boletas para todas elecciones por correo autom√°ticamente.</p>\n\n<h3>1. Es f√°cil.</h3>\n\n<p>Se puede registrar como Votante Permanente por Correo <a href="http://www.sos.ca.gov/elections/vote-by-mail/pdf/fill-in-vote-by-mail-app-instruct.pdf">llenando esta sencilla forma</a>.\nLos votantes del condado de Los √Ångeles deben enviar por correo la forma debidamente llenada a:\nDean Logan, Registrar - Recorder/County Clerk\nP.O. Box 1024\nNorwalk, CA 90651-1024</p>\n\n<h3>2. Es conveniente.</h3>\n\n<p>Usted no tiene que arreglarse para salir o buscar d√≥nde est√° la casilla para votar. S√≥lo tiene que llenar la boleta en la tranquilidad de su casa a la hora que sea m√°s conveniente para usted.</p>\n\n<h3>3. Nunca olvidar√° una elecci√≥n.</h3>\n\n<p>Su gu√≠a de votante y su boleta electoral llegar√°n autom√°ticamente por correo un par de semanas antes de la elecci√≥n.</p>\n\n<h3>4.¬°En la vida pasan cosas inesperadas!</h3>\n\n<p>No deje que esto le impida que su voto cuente. Al votar de manera temprana, usted puede prevenir que una emergencia en el trabajo o un hijo enfermo le impida ir a las urnas el d√≠a de la votaci√≥n. ¬°Aseg√∫rese de que su voto cuente! ¬°Vote antes! ¬°Vote por correo! No se preocupe, si usted olvida enviar por correo su boleta antes del d√≠a de la elecci√≥n, puede llevarla a la casilla de votaci√≥n y entregarla en persona.</p>\n', '4 Grandes razones para votar por correo', '¬øSab√≠a que se puede votar por correo? En California, se puede registrar para recibir su boleta para la pr√≥xima elecci√≥n por correo o se puede registrarse como Votante Permanente por Correo para recibir sus boletas para todas elecciones por correo autom√°ticamente.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '228-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '', 228, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/228-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(971, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '<p>This interactive training session will brief parents on the basics of charter schools and the charter school movement in California.  Parents will also learn and practice sharing their personal story and experience with charter schools. This is a great intro for charter parents to encourage and enhance their advocacy skills. This session will also build their confidence when speaking in the community and media regarding their school and the charter movement.\n- <a href="/FTC_IE_parent_workshop_flyer.pdf">Printable flyer to spread the word at your school</a></p>\n\n<h3>Date</h3>\n\n<p>Wednesday, April 24th, 2013</p>\n\n<h3>Time</h3>\n\n<p>6:00pm to 7:00 p.m.</p>\n\n<h3>Location</h3>\n\n<p>Excel Prep Charter School\n23750 Alessandro Blvd., Moreno Valley CA, 92553\n<a href="mailto:vkoss@calcharters.org">RSVP to Valieria Koss.</a>\n<em>Refreshments Provided</em></p>\n', 'April 24: Free Inland Empire Parent Workshop', 'Parents are invited to a great training including Charter Schools 101 & Sharing Your Story\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '226-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '', 226, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/226-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(972, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '<p>You are cordially invited to attend the first in a series of FREE parent engagement workshops, hosted by the California State University, African American Initiative - in partnership with Educate California.\nThese workshops are designed to provide families with the most current and effective tools and resources for preparing students for college, careers and life after high school. Each family will receive materials and information to empower them to advocate for the child(rens) K-12 education.\n- <a href="https://events.r20.constantcontact.com/register/eventReg?llr=gjasvrn6&amp;oeidk=a07e79mwfngc669ad3c&amp;oseq=a02asngll5xgez">Register Now!</a></p>\n\n<h3>Event Details</h3>\n\n<p>Saturday May 25, 2013 from 10:00 AM to 1:00 PM PDT\nREGISTRATION: 9:00 AM\nCalifornia State University, Los Angeles\n5151 State University Drive\nUniversity Student Union Theater\nLos Angeles, CA 90032\nLimited space is available and families will be served on a first-come basis. Please register early and encourage others to do the same.</p>\n', 'May 25: Free LifePrep Academy Workshop for Parents in Los Angeles', 'You are cordially invited to attend the first in a series of FREE parent engagement workshops, hosted by the California State University, African American Initiative - in partnership with Educate California.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '225-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '', 225, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/225-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(973, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '<p>Ay√∫denos a difundir informaci√≥n mediante la inclusi√≥n de nuestras noticias en su bolet√≠n escolar o en su p√°gina web.</p>\n\n<h3>Elecci√≥n Importante para la Junta Escolar en el 21 de Mayo</h3>\n\n<p>En el 21 de mayo, los votantes del este del Valle de San Fernando tendr√°n la oportunidad de votar para la persona que va a representarnos en la Junta Directiva del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los √Ångeles (LAUSD). Esta es una elecci√≥n muy importante no solo para nuestra escuela sino para el futuro de la educaci√≥n p√∫blica en Los Angeles.\nLos miembros de la Junta Directiva toman decisiones que afectan a nuestros ni√±os y nuestras escuelas. Incluyen si se renovar√° el permiso a nuestras escuelas o se cerrar√°n y si una nueva escuela ch√°rter puede abrir. Tambi√©n vigilan c√≥mo operan nuestras escuelas ch√°rter, desde los programas de educaci√≥n especial hasta el presupuesto.\nAlentamos a todos informarse sobre la elecci√≥n y ¬°Votemos el 21 de mayo!\n<strong>El 6 de mayo el la fecha limite para registrarse para votar.</strong> El 6 de mayo la fecha l√≠mite para registrarse para votar. Tenemos los formularios en la oficina de la escuela. Usted puede registrarse para votar en l√≠nea en www.sos.ca.gov o puede tambi√©n recoger un formulario en la oficina electoral de su condado, bibliotecas locales, u oficinas de correo.\nAprende m√°s en <a href="/la2013">www.ccsafamilies/la2013</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>Important LA School Board Election on May 21</h3>\n\n<p>On May 25, families in the east San Fernando Valley have the opportunity to vote for who will represent our community on the Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD) board. This is a very important election, not only for our school but for the future of our public schools and parent choice in Los Angeles.\nThe board makes major decisions that affect our school and our kids. This includes whether our charter school will be renewed and whether new charter schools can open and they have oversight of how our charter school is run - special education, budget and more.\nWe encourage everyone to get informed about this important election and to vote on May 21!\n<strong>May 6 is the deadline to register to vote.</strong> If you aren\'t already registered, we have forms in our school office. You can also easily register to vote online at www.sos.ca.gov or by picking up a form at your county elections office, library, or U.S. Post Office.\nLearn more at <a href="/la2013">www.ccsafamilies.org/la2013</a>.</p>\n', 'Para Su Bolet√≠n: Elecci√≥n Importante para la Junta Escolar de Los Angeles en el 21 de Mayo', 'Ay√∫denos a difundir informaci√≥n mediante la inclusi√≥n de nuestras noticias en su bolet√≠n escolar o en su p√°gina web.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '223-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '', 223, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/223-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(974, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '<h3>Cumbre de Padres en San Diego</h3>\n\n<p>M√°s de 300 padres que representan a m√°s de 50 escuelas ch√°rter en todo el estado, desde Chico hasta San Diego, se reunieron para participar en nuestra Cumbre de Padres a mediados de marzo. Escuchamos historias inspiradoras y aprendimos mucho de los presentadores y de cada uno.\nLa primera Cumbre de Padres se llev√≥ a cabo en 2009 y ahora es parte regular de la Conferencia Anual de Escuelas Ch√°rter de California que atrajo a San Diego a m√°s de 3,000 maestros y l√≠deres de escuelas ch√°rter este a√±o.\nAlgunos de los puntos importantes de la Cumbre de Padres de 2013:\nEl d√≠a se inici√≥ con la bienvenida que dieron Richard Barrera, miembro de la Junta de Educaci√≥n del Distrito Unificado de San Diego y Jed Wallace, presidente y director general ejecutivo de la Asociaci√≥n de Escuelas Ch√°rter de California. Los padres se unieron a la sesi√≥n de la conferencia general, donde Corri Ravare, directora ejecutiva de Families That Can, tom√≥ la palabra para compartir el entusiasta trabajo que hacen los padres a nivel estatal con m√°s de 2,000 l√≠deres y maestros de las escuelas ch√°rter. La oradora  principal fue Michelle Rhee, de Students First.\nDurante la tarde, los padres asistieron a una amplia gama de sesiones que abarcaron desde comunicaciones para apoyar a su hijo hacia el √©xito hasta c√≥mo leer la informaci√≥n de las escuelas y la importancia de la labor de defensa de los padres. Joe Morales, de la escuela primaria Desert Trails, inspir√≥ a los padres con su historia acerca de c√≥mo se uni√≥ con otros padres de familia para usar el poder de √©stos para mejorar la escuela de sus hijos. Finalizamos el d√≠a con la celebraci√≥n del 20 aniversario de las escuelas ch√°rter de California con un pastel de cumplea√±os, ¬°por supuesto!\n¬°Aparten la fecha! La Cumbre de Padres 2014 se llevar√° a cabo durante la semana del 5 de marzo de 2014 en San Jose, CA. Por favor permanezcan en contacto con su representante de Families That Can si usted quiere enviar padres a la Cumbre de Padres del pr√≥ximo a√±o.\n- <a href="http://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.486834038049387.1073741827.102530249813103&amp;type=1">Vea las fotos.</a></p>\n\n<h3>Parent Summit 2013 in San Diego</h3>\n\n<p>More than 300 parents representing over 50 charter schools stretching across the state from Chico to San Diego came together for our Parent Summit in mid-March. Parents shared inspiring stories and learned a lot from the presenters and each other.\nThe first Parent Summit was held in 2009 and is now a regular part of the Annual California Charter Schools Conference, which attracted more than 3,000 charter school leaders and teachers to San Diego this year.\nSome of the highlights of the 2013 Parent Summit included hearing from Richard Barrera, a member of the San Diego Unified Board of Education, and Jed Wallace, President and CEO of the California Charter Schools Association. Parents joined the conference general session where Corri Ravare, Executive Director of Families That Can, took to the main stage to share the exciting work parents are doing statewide with more than 2,000 charter leaders and teachers. The key note speaker was Michelle Rhee of Students First.\nFor the afternoon, parents attended a range of sessions on everything from communications to supporting your child to success to how to read school data to the importance of parent advocacy. Joe Morales from Desert Trails Elementary School in Adelanto inspired parents with his story of how he joined with fellow parents to use the parent trigger to turn around his children\'s school. The day wrapped up with a celebration of the 20th anniversary of California charter schools - with birthday cake of course!\nSave the date! The 2014 Parent Summit will be held during the week of March 5, 2014 in San Jose, CA.  Please stay in contact with <a href="/contact.html">your Families That Can representative</a> if you are interested in attending next year.\n- <a href="http://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.486834038049387.1073741827.102530249813103&amp;type=1">See photos.</a></p>\n', 'Para Su Bolet√≠n: Cumbre de Padres 2013 en San Diego', 'Ay√∫denos a difundir informaci√≥n mediante la inclusi√≥n de nuestras noticias en su bolet√≠n escolar o en su p√°gina web.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '222-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '', 222, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/222-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(975, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '<p>Charter school staff and families get it at a discounted rate for the Padres game - print the flyer with all the details. Local charter schools will have the opportunity to have a student be the \'Play Ball\' kid and selected schools will also be recognized on the field in the pre-game ceremony.\n- <a href="/San_Diego_Padres_Charter_School_Day_Flyer_2013.pdf">Charter School Appreciation Night Flyer</a></p>\n', 'May 4: Charter School Appreciation Night at Petco Park!', 'Charter school staff and families get it at a discounted rate for the Padres game - print the flyer with all the details.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '221-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '', 221, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/221-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(976, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '<div class="figure embedded-image none"><img alt="capitol_horizontal_stock.jpg (Entry/Page Lead Image)" src="/assets_c/2012/03/capitol_horizontal_stock-cropped-proto-ftc_theme___lead.jpg" width="612" height="269" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></div>\n\n<p>Este mayo, CCSA celebrar√° la Semana Nacional de las Escuelas Ch√°rter y el 20 Aniversario de las Escuelas Ch√°rter con nuestro D√≠a de la Defensa en Sacramento. L√≠deres de las escuelas ch√°rter y padres como usted est√°n invitados a ir al Capitolio Estatal para un emocionante d√≠a en el que se reunir√°n con legisladores estatales para  hablar sobre los importantes problemas que enfrentan las escuelas ch√°rter.\nEste a√±o esperamos que participen m√°s padres que nunca. A quienes asistan se les obsequiar√° un almuerzo en una tienda de campa√±a privada en la Escalinata Oeste del hermoso edificio del Capitolio de California. Como siempre, habr√° tiempo para establecer conexiones con otros padres l√≠deres y recorrer el Capitolio, si es que no lo han hecho antes. Es una gran oportunidad para contar la historia de su escuela ch√°rter y ayudar a nuestros legisladores estatales a saber m√°s acerca de las escuelas ch√°rter.\nFamilies That Can y CCSA le dar√°n el entrenamiento y el apoyo que usted necesita para convertirse en un Campe√≥n Ch√°rter seguro de s√≠ mismo. Organizaremos un seminario de entrenamiento por Internet s√≥lo para padres y  habr√° materiales con informaci√≥n sobre los asuntos que afectan a las ch√°rter este a√±o. Le daremos las herramientas que usted necesita para que sea un d√≠a de gran √©xito en el Capitolio.</p>\n\n<h3>Reg√≠strese ahora para el D√≠a de la Defensa 2013</h3>\n\n<p><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/2011/03/advocacy-day-registration-form.html">Descargue aqu√≠ una forma para registrarse hoy</a>. Cuando la complete, por favor entregue la forma seleccionando el bot√≥n "Submit Form" que se encuentra en la esquina superior derecha del documento. Usted recibir√° la confirmaci√≥n de que su registro ha sido recibido. Conforme se acerque el D√≠a de la Defensa, nuestro equipo de Asuntos Gubernamentales le  ofrecer√° un calendario y todos los materiales que usted necesite para prepararse para ese d√≠a. Por favor, no dude en contactar a <a href="mailto:nbautista@calcharters.org">Nicole Virga Bautista</a> para cualquier pregunta.\n¬øNo puede ir al D√≠a de la Defensa? <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/advocacy/schedule-legislative-visit.html">Aprenda aqu√≠ c√≥mo programar una visita legislativa</a></p>\n', '¬°√önase a nosotros para el D√≠a de la Defensa el 8 de mayo en Sacramento!', 'Este mayo, CCSA celebrar√° la Semana Nacional de las Escuelas Ch√°rter y el 20 Aniversario de las Escuelas Ch√°rter con nuestro D√≠a de la Defensa en Sacramento. L√≠deres de las escuelas ch√°rter y padres como usted est√°n invitados a ir al Capitolio Estatal para un emocionante d√≠a en el que se reunir√°n con legisladores estatales para  hablar sobre los importantes problemas que enfrentan las escuelas ch√°rter.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '220-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '', 220, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/220-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(977, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '<p>In 2010, a group of parents from Compton made history when they were the first in the nation to use a new California law called the "parent trigger." Under the law, if over half of the parents at a low-performing school sign a petition, the school district must implement the policy they choose to improve the school.\nA team of filmmakers in Los Angeles followed the parents and guardians of McKinley Elementary School for nearly two years to tell this story of parent empowerment - a story about everyday parents who took an extraordinary stand for their children.\nThe filmmakers hope to be able to host screenings for parents and community members and to distribute the film more widely.\n- <a href="http://www.wetheparentsfilm.com">See the trailer for "We the Parents" and learn more. </a></p>\n', 'New Film Highlights Parent Power', 'In 2010, a group of parents from Compton made history when they were the first in the nation to use a new California law called the "parent trigger."\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '218-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '2016-01-13 04:22:16', '', 218, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/218-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(978, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '<p>En 2010, un grupo de padres de Compton hicieron historia cuando fueron los primeros en el pa√≠s en usar una nueva ley de California llamada "parent trigger". Bajo la ley, si m√°s de la mitad de los padres de una escuela de bajo desempe√±o firman una petici√≥n, el distrito escolar debe implementar la pol√≠tica que ellos elijan para mejorar la escuela.\nUn grupo de cineastas en Los √Ångeles sigui√≥ a los padres y tutores de la escuela primaria McKinley durante casi dos a√±os para contar esta historia de empoderamiento de los padres, que habla acerca de padres comunes que hacen una extraordinaria defensa de sus hijos.\nLos cineastas esperan poder organizar presentaciones del filme para padres de familia y miembros de la comunidad y distribuir la pel√≠cula de manera m√°s amplia.\n<a href="http://www.wetheparentsfilm.com">Vean el trailer de "We the Parents" y conozcan m√°s de esta pel√≠cula.</a></p>\n', 'Un nuevo filme destaca el poder de los padres', 'En 2010, un grupo de padres de Compton hicieron historia cuando fueron los primeros en el pa√≠s en usar una nueva ley de California llamada "parent trigger".\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '217-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '', 217, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/217-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(979, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '<div class="figure embedded-image none"><img alt="FTC_cross-charter_workshop_san_diego.JPG (Entry/Page Lead Image)" src="/assets_c/2013/03/FTC_cross-charter_workshop_san_diego-cropped-proto-ftc_theme___lead.jpg" width="612" height="269" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></div>\n\n<p>Los padres de familia de m√°s de seis escuelas, entre ellas Preuss School en UCSD y Literacy First, participaron en el Nivel 1 del Entrenamiento de Defensa. Tambi√©n participaron padres interesados en enviar a sus hijos a escuelas ch√°rter. Nuestro anfitri√≥n de la tarde fue Old Town Academy y los padres recibieron una maravillosa presentaci√≥n por parte del fundador de la escuela y l√≠der Tom Donahue, quien describi√≥ el innovador curr√≠culum en el que se incluye tecnolog√≠a, m√∫sica y un programa de rob√≥tica.\nEl verdadero entusiasmo lleg√≥ durante la interesante sesi√≥n de preguntas y respuestas, cuando los padres elaboraron estrategias para eliminar mitos acerca de las escuelas ch√°rter. Tambi√©n trabajaron en estrategias para usar herramientas en sus propias comunidades y en  los medios de comunicaci√≥n para rechazar esos mitos y compartir la verdadera informaci√≥n sobre  las escuelas ch√°rter. Durante el componente final del entrenamiento se les permiti√≥ a los padres compartir sus historias con el grupo.\n"Fue realmente incre√≠ble ser testigo de primera mano del poder de esos padres al compartir sus historias y trabajamos en equipo para encontrar estrategias sobre c√≥mo compartir esas historias", dijo Valieria Koss,  coordinadora de Parent and Family Engagement de Families That Can. "Como padres, sus historias tienen un enorme impacto en el movimiento ch√°rter".\nFamilies That Can organizar√° m√°s talleres en el condado de Orange y en Inland Empire en los pr√≥ximos meses.</p>\n', 'El primer taller de escuelas ch√°rter de todo San Diego, un √©xito', 'Todav√≠a con el recuerdo del entusiasmo causado por la Cumbre de Padres realizada el mi√©rcoles 27 de marzo, un grupo de entusiasmados padres de familia del condado de San Diego se reuni√≥ para participar en el primer Entrenamiento de Defensa de Families That Can para abogar por las escuelas ch√°rter.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '215-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '', 215, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/215-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(980, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '<p>More than 300 parents representing over 50 charter schools stretching across the state from Chico to San Diego came together for our Parent Summit in mid-March. Parents shared inspiring stories and learned a lot from the presenters and each other.\nThe first Parent Summit was held in 2009 and is now a regular part of the Annual California Charter Schools Conference, which attracted more than 3,000 charter school leaders and teachers to San Diego this year.\nSome of the highlights of the 2013 Parent Summit included hearing from Richard Barrera, a member of the San Diego Unified Board of Education, and Jed Wallace, President and CEO of the California Charter Schools Association. Parents joined the conference general session where Corri Ravare, Executive Director of Families That Can, took to the main stage to share the exciting work parents are doing statewide with more than 2,000 charter leaders and teachers. The key note speaker was Michelle Rhee of Students First.\nFor the afternoon, parents attended a range of sessions on everything from communications to supporting your child to success to how to read school data to the importance of parent advocacy. Joe Morales from Desert Trails Elementary School in Adelanto inspired parents with his story of how he joined with fellow parents to use the parent trigger to turn around his children\'s school. The day wrapped up with a celebration of the 20th anniversary of California charter schools - with birthday cake of course!\nSave the date! The 2014 Parent Summit will be held during the week of March 5, 2014 in San Jose, CA.  Please stay in contact with <a href="/contact.html">your Families That Can representative</a> if you are interested in attending next year.\n- <a href="http://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.486834038049387.1073741827.102530249813103&amp;type=1">See photos.</a></p>\n\n<h3>Cumbre de Padres en San Diego</h3>\n\n<p>M√°s de 300 padres que representan a m√°s de 50 escuelas ch√°rter en todo el estado, desde Chico hasta San Diego, se reunieron para participar en nuestra Cumbre de Padres a mediados de marzo. Escuchamos historias inspiradoras y aprendimos mucho de los presentadores y de cada uno.\nLa primera Cumbre de Padres se llev√≥ a cabo en 2009 y ahora es parte regular de la Conferencia Anual de Escuelas Ch√°rter de California que atrajo a San Diego a m√°s de 3,000 maestros y l√≠deres de escuelas ch√°rter este a√±o.\nAlgunos de los puntos importantes de la Cumbre de Padres de 2013:\nEl d√≠a se inici√≥ con la bienvenida que dieron Richard Barrera, miembro de la Junta de Educaci√≥n del Distrito Unificado de San Diego y Jed Wallace, presidente y director general ejecutivo de la Asociaci√≥n de Escuelas Ch√°rter de California. Los padres se unieron a la sesi√≥n de la conferencia general, donde Corri Ravare, directora ejecutiva de Families That Can, tom√≥ la palabra para compartir el entusiasta trabajo que hacen los padres a nivel estatal con m√°s de 2,000 l√≠deres y maestros de las escuelas ch√°rter. La oradora  principal fue Michelle Rhee, de Students First.\nDurante la tarde, los padres asistieron a una amplia gama de sesiones que abarcaron desde comunicaciones para apoyar a su hijo hacia el √©xito hasta c√≥mo leer la informaci√≥n de las escuelas y la importancia de la labor de defensa de los padres. Joe Morales, de la escuela primaria Desert Trails, inspir√≥ a los padres con su historia acerca de c√≥mo se uni√≥ con otros padres de familia para usar el poder de √©stos para mejorar la escuela de sus hijos. Finalizamos el d√≠a con la celebraci√≥n del 20 aniversario de las escuelas ch√°rter de California con un pastel de cumplea√±os, ¬°por supuesto!\n¬°Aparten la fecha! La Cumbre de Padres 2014 se llevar√° a cabo durante la semana del 5 de marzo de 2014 en San Jose, CA. Por favor permanezcan en contacto con su representante de Families That Can si usted quiere enviar padres a la Cumbre de Padres del pr√≥ximo a√±o.\nM√°s de 300 padres que representan a m√°s de 50 escuelas ch√°rter en todo el estado, desde Chico hasta San Diego, se reunieron para participar en nuestra Cumbre de Padres a mediados de marzo. Escuchamos historias inspiradoras y aprendimos mucho de los presentadores y de cada uno.\nLa primera Cumbre de Padres se llev√≥ a cabo en 2009 y ahora es parte regular de la Conferencia Anual de Escuelas Ch√°rter de California que atrajo a San Diego a m√°s de 3,000 maestros y l√≠deres de escuelas ch√°rter este a√±o.\nAlgunos de los puntos importantes de la Cumbre de Padres de 2013:\nEl d√≠a se inici√≥ con la bienvenida que dieron Richard Barrera, miembro de la Junta de Educaci√≥n del Distrito Unificado de San Diego y Jed Wallace, presidente y director general ejecutivo de la Asociaci√≥n de Escuelas Ch√°rter de California. Los padres se unieron a la sesi√≥n de la conferencia general, donde Corri Ravare, directora ejecutiva de Families That Can, tom√≥ la palabra para compartir el entusiasta trabajo que hacen los padres a nivel estatal con m√°s de 2,000 l√≠deres y maestros de las escuelas ch√°rter. La oradora  principal fue Michelle Rhee, de Students First.\nDurante la tarde, los padres asistieron a una amplia gama de sesiones que abarcaron desde comunicaciones para apoyar a su hijo hacia el √©xito hasta c√≥mo leer la informaci√≥n de las escuelas y la importancia de la labor de defensa de los padres. Joe Morales, de la escuela primaria Desert Trails, inspir√≥ a los padres con su historia acerca de c√≥mo se uni√≥ con otros padres de familia para usar el poder de √©stos para mejorar la escuela de sus hijos. Finalizamos el d√≠a con la celebraci√≥n del 20 aniversario de las escuelas ch√°rter de California con un pastel de cumplea√±os, ¬°por supuesto!\n¬°Aparten la fecha! La Cumbre de Padres 2014 se llevar√° a cabo durante la semana del 5 de marzo de 2014 en San Jose, CA. Por favor permanezcan en contacto con su representante de Families That Can si usted quiere enviar padres a la Cumbre de Padres del pr√≥ximo a√±o.</p>\n', 'For Your Newsletter: Parent Summit 2013 in San Diego', 'Did parents from your school participate this year? Share a photo and this article in your parent newsletter!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '214-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '', 214, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/214-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(981, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '<div class="figure embedded-image none"><img alt="FTC_cross-charter_workshop_san_diego.JPG (Entry/Page Lead Image)" src="/assets_c/2013/03/FTC_cross-charter_workshop_san_diego-cropped-proto-ftc_theme___lead.jpg" width="612" height="269" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></div>\n\n<p>Still reeling from the enthusiasm of Parent Summit on Wednesday March 27, excited parents from across San Diego County joined together to participate in the first ever cross-charter Families That Can Advocacy Training.  Parents from over six schools participated in the Level 1 Advocacy Training, including the Preuss School at UCSD, Literacy First and parents interested in sending their children to charter schools.  Our host for the evening was Old Town Academy and parents were treated to a wonderful introduction from the school\'s founder and leader Tom Donahue who described the innovative curriculum infused with technology, music as well as a robotics program they implement on campus.\nThe real excitement came during the engaging and challenging Q &amp; A session when parents worked out strategies for dispelling charter school myths and tools to use in their own communities and in the media to defeat these myths and share the facts about charter schools.  The final component of the training allowed parents to share their story with the group.\n"It was truly amazing to witness first-hand the power of these parents as their stories were shared and we worked as a team to figure out strategies for sharing these stories," said Valieria Koss, Parent and Family Engagement Coordinator for Families That Can.  "As parents, their stories can have a huge impact on the charter movement."\nFamilies That Can will be hosting more workshops in Orange County and the Inland Empire in the coming months.</p>\n', 'First-ever Cross-charter Workshop in San Diego is a Success', 'Parents from across San Diego County joined together to participate in the first ever cross-charter Families That Can Advocacy Training, hosted at Old Town Academy.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '213-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '', 213, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/213-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(982, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '<div class="figure embedded-image none"><img alt="parent_summit_group_photo_2013.JPG (Entry/Page Lead Image)" src="/assets_c/2013/03/parent_summit_group_photo_2013-cropped-proto-ftc_theme___lead.jpg" width="612" height="269" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></div>\n\n<p>More than 300 parents representing over 50 charter schools stretching across the state from Chico to San Diego came together for our Parent Summit in mid-March. We heard inspiring stories and learned a lot from the presenters and each other.\nThe first Parent Summit was held in 2009 and is now a regular part of the Annual California Charter Schools Conference, which attracted more than 3,000 charter school leaders and teachers to San Diego this year.\n- <a href="http://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.486834038049387.1073741827.102530249813103&amp;type=1">See photos.</a>\nSome of the highlights of the 2013 Parent Summit:\n- The day kicked off with a welcome from both Richard Barrera, a member of the San Diego Unified Board of Education, and Jed Wallace, President and CEO of the California Charter Schools Association.\n- Parents joined the conference general session where Corri Ravare, Executive Director of Families That Can, took to the main stage to share the exciting work parents are doing statewide with more than 2,000 charter leaders and teachers.\n- The key note speaker was Michelle Rhee of Students First. Our favorite quote was: "More mothers should be superintendents." <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=82BtE5gloI8&amp;list=PLkzM8Ek4bMGcJrwbP_FhBWihgw3VXJ8cB&amp;index=22">See the video.</a>\n- There were several major awards presented, including the Volunteers of the Year, Charter School of the Year and more! <a href="http://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLkzM8Ek4bMGcJrwbP_FhBWihgw3VXJ8cB">See the videos.</a>\n- For the afternoon, parents attended a range of sessions on everything from communications to supporting your child to success to how to read school data to the importance of parent advocacy.\n- Joe Morales from Desert Trails Elementary School inspired parents with his story of how he joined with fellow parents to use the parent trigger to turn around his children\'s school. <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5zRvJ8DAe-U">Check out this video of what he had to say.</a>\n- We wrapped up the day by celebrating the 20th anniversary of California charter schools - with birthday cake of course!\nWhat did you think of the Parent Summit? Send your comments to us!</p>\n\n<h4>What parents said about the summit:</h4>\n\n<p><em>I learned how to defend our charter school because some people speak badly of charter schools. When other parents say something bad of our school, I now know how to answer. From the way we were taken to San Diego and in the way Families That Can prepared their agendas and workshops, I know they had a great desire (ganas) to help us parents. When I got back, I knew I wanted to help other parents so I have been telling them to go to the Parent Forums and if they see that their kids need tutoring, to make sure to develop their strength to tell their teachers. I would love to go again to another parent conference. It has changed the way I think.</em>\nOlga Coronado, Vaughn Next Century Learning Center\n<em>I had a wonderful time and an awesome experience taking in all of the workshops. I am already using it with my kids and the kids of other parents. I was inspired by the other parents\' stories and I would love to use what they learned.</em>\nElvia Teck, Vaughn Next Century Learning Center\n<em>The information they offered was very helpful for the parents. They were helping parents understand that the school can be a better place with our help. They gave us specific information regarding the laws and our schools, and what schools must follow. They gave us the tools, now all we have to do is use them.</em>\nAngeles Rojas, Vaughn Next Century Learning Center\n<em>For this event, I left work and it was rough because I have my own business but I\'m glad I made the effort. You have to invest a lot of time to have a good school. Everyone should help out. This would solve problems.  I would like to see this training brought to the school.</em>\nAlfonso Salazar, Vaughn Next Century Learning Center\n<em>The whole experience made me feel proud to be part of the charter world and thankful too, because it allowed me to see how hard all of the leaders and administrators work to keep the schools going. I appreciate the charters more so after I heard all of these stories.</em>\nKristina  Briones, Vaughn Next Century Learning Center\n<em>The conference recharged my batteries and it gave me more of a desire to help the charter schools more. We had the chance to meet the "Volunteers of the Year" after their presentation. They were very kind people. We understand why they do what they do to help their school. We never thought about it before but we were able to relate to their story. It made us feel good regarding the work we do here at our school.</em>\nBrenda Lemus, Vaughn Next Century Learning Center\nWhat parent leaders said about the summit:\n<em>Our parents were over the moon with excitement over the whole experience. We are so pleased that an opportunity like this was possible with Families That Can and are grateful for our partnership. We look forward to working together and expanding our efforts together.  Everyone had an amazing time.</em>\n- Julieta Ya√±ez, Parent Outreach Coordinator, Los Angeles Leadership Academy\n<em>Our parents came back enthusiastic, inspired and motivated. They really enjoyed the experience of Parent Summit - especially when all the parents were recognized at the conference for the contributions they make to the school. We\'re putting together a presentation so that the parents can all go back to their school sites and share the learning with the other families.</em>\nZulma Suro, Director Whole Child, Camino Nuevo</p>\n\n<h3>Save the date!</h3>\n\n<p>The 2014 Parent Summit will be held during the week of March 5, 2014 in San Jose, CA.  Please stay in contact with <a href="/contact.html">your Families That Can representative</a> if you\'d like to send your parents to Parent Summit next year.</p>\n\n<h3>Schools Represented in 2013</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Alliance College-Ready Public Schools</li>\n<li>America\'s Finest Charter School</li>\n<li>Aspire Antonio Maria Lugo Academy</li>\n<li>Aspire Lionel Wilson College Preparatory Academy</li>\n<li>Blue Oak Charter School</li>\n<li>CHAMPS - Charter High School of Arts</li>\n<li>Classical Academies</li>\n<li>Camino Nuevo Charter Academy -  Burlington</li>\n<li>Camino Nuevo Charter Academy -  Castellanos</li>\n<li>Camino Nuevo Charter Academy -  Cisneros</li>\n<li>Camino Nuevo Charter Academy -  High School</li>\n<li>Community Collaborative CS</li>\n<li>Crown Preparatory Academy</li>\n<li>Da Vinci K8</li>\n<li>Education for Change</li>\n<li>Equitas Academy</li>\n<li>Excel Charter Prep Charter School</li>\n<li>Fenton Public Charter Schools</li>\n<li>Futuro Prep</li>\n<li>Gabriella Charter School</li>\n<li>Global Education Academy</li>\n<li>Gompers Preparatory Academy</li>\n<li>Green Dot Public Schools</li>\n<li>ICEF Lou Dantzler Prep. Middle School</li>\n<li>JJMS</li>\n<li>JJMS Phoenix</li>\n<li>Juanita Tate Elementary School</li>\n<li>Keiller Leadership Acadamy</li>\n<li>King Chavez Neighborhood of Schools</li>\n<li>Language Academy of Sacramento</li>\n<li>Leonardo Da Vinci Health Sciences</li>\n<li>Liberty First Charter School</li>\n<li>Lighthouse Community Charter School</li>\n<li>Los Angeles Leadership Academy</li>\n<li>Magnolia Science Academy 4 - Venice</li>\n<li>Magnolia Science Academy 1</li>\n<li>Pacific Technology School-Santa Ana</li>\n<li>Para Los Ninos Charter Schools</li>\n<li>Extera Charter School</li>\n<li>PCS2013</li>\n<li>People Acting in Community Together</li>\n<li>Preuss</li>\n<li>PS7 Elementary</li>\n<li>Public Safety Academy-San Bernardino</li>\n<li>Rocketship Alma Academy</li>\n<li>Rocketship Los Suenos</li>\n<li>Sacramento Charter High School</li>\n<li>Santa Monica Blvd. Community Charter School</li>\n<li>Semillas del Pueblo</li>\n<li>Steele Canyon</li>\n<li>Synergy Kinetic</li>\n<li>Urban Discovery Academy</li>\n<li>Vaughn Next Century Learning Center</li>\n<li>Vincent Academy</li>\n<li>Vista Charter Middle School</li>\n<li>Voices College-Bound Language Academy</li>\n<li>Watts Learning Center Charter School</li>\n<li>Wisdom Academy for Young Scientists</li>\n<li>YES Charter Academy</li>\n</ul>\n', 'Highlights and Photos from the 2013 Parent Summit', 'More than 300 parents representing over 50 schools charter schools stretching across the state from Chico to San Diego came together for our Parent Summit in mid-March. We heard inspiring stories and learned a lot from the presenters and each other.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '212-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '', 212, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/212-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(983, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '<p>Thousands of charter school parents voted, volunteered and spoke out to make an impact in the important Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD) board primary election on March 5, 2013. Three of the seven seats were up for election March 5. Current Board President Monica Garcia won re-election, as did Boardmember Steve Zimmer.  In Board District 6, which covers the east San Fernando Valley, there will be a run-off on May 21 between candidates Antonio Sanchez and Monica Ratliff.\n"It was good to see parents encouraging other parents to vote, spreading the word about the election at their school and hosting forums for the candidates," says Corri Tate Ravare, Executive Director of Families That Can.  "The charter school community came out in force."\nLocal school boards make major decisions that affect our schools - from deciding whether new charters can open to whether current charters can stay open or what facilities charter schools receive. Nearly one out of 5 charter schools in California is located in LAUSD, making this an especially important election.\n- <a href="/2013/03/decision-2013-los-angeles-unified-board-district-lausd-elections.html">Check out our Elections Toolkit with everything you need to spread the word at your school!</a>\nLearn more about the candidates:\n- <a href="/2013/02/video-la-school-board-candidate-forum.html">Video from the Families That Can Candidate Forum at Vaughn Next Century Learning Center</a>\n- <a href="/2013/02/lausd-candidate-guide-for-east-san-fernando-valley.html">Board District 6 Candidate Guide</a></p>\n', '1,000s of Charter Parents Mobilize for LA School Board Primary Election', 'Thousands of charter school parents voted, volunteered and spoke out to make an impact in the important Los Angeles Unified School District (LAUSD) board primary election. It\'s not over yet! Find out about the election coming up May 21.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '211-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '', 211, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/211-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(984, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '<div class="figure embedded-image none"><img alt="capitol_horizontal_stock.jpg (Entry/Page Lead Image)" src="/assets_c/2012/03/capitol_horizontal_stock-cropped-proto-ftc_theme___lead.jpg" width="612" height="269" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></div>\n\n<p>This May, CCSA will celebrate National Charter Schools Week and the 20th Anniversary of Charter Schools with our annual Advocacy Day in Sacramento. Charter leaders and parents like you are invited to come to the State Capitol for an exciting day meeting with State Legislators on the important issues facing charter schools.\nThis year we hope to have more parents participating than ever. You will be treated to lunch in a private tent on the West Steps of the beautiful California State Capitol Building. As always, there\'ll be time to network with other parent leaders, and tour the Capitol if you haven\'t been before. It\'s a great opportunity to tell your charter story and help our State Legislators learn more about charter schools.\nFamilies That Can and CCSA will help you get the training and support you need to be a confident Charter Champion. We will host a training webinar just for parents, plus materials with information on the issues affecting charter schools this year.  We will give you the tools you need to have a successful day in the Capitol</p>\n\n<h2>Register now for Advocacy Day 2013</h2>\n\n<p><a href="http://www.ccsa.org/2011/03/advocacy-day-registration-form.html">Download a registration form today.</a>  When complete, please submit the form by selecting "Submit Form" in the upper right hand corner of the document.  You will receive confirmation that your registration has been received.  As Advocacy Day approaches our Government Affairs team will provide you with a schedule and all the materials you need in preparation for the day.  Please feel free to contact <a href="mailto:nbautista@calcharters.org">Nicole Virga Bautista</a> with any questions.\nCan\'t join us for Advocacy Day?  <a href="http://www.ccsa.org/advocacy/schedule-legislative-visit.html">Learn how to schedule a legislative visit.</a></p>\n', 'Join us for Advocacy Day May 8th in Sacramento!', 'This May, CCSA will celebrate National Charter Schools Week and the 20th Anniversary of Charter Schools with our annual Advocacy Day in Sacramento. Tell your charter school story!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '210-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '2016-01-13 04:22:17', '', 210, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/210-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
