(1010, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:20', '2016-01-13 04:22:20', '<p>En el 21 de mayo, los votantes del este del Valle de San Fernando tienen la oportunidad para votar por su representante en la Junta Directiva del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los √Ångeles (LAUSD).\n¬°Nosotros decidimos el futuro de la educaci√≥n en Los Angeles!\n- <a href="/cgi-bin/mt/mt-search.cgi?blog_id=10&amp;tag=LAUSD%202013%20en%20Espa√±ol&amp;limit=20">Lea las ultimas noticias.</a>\n- <a href="/2013/02/una-guia-para-los-padres-sobre-elecciones.html">Una Gu√≠a Para Los Padres Sobre Elecciones</a>\n- <a href="http://laschoolboard.org/sites/default/files/images/maps/2007-08%20Board%20District%206.pdf">Mapa del Distrito - Area 6</a></p>\n\n<h3>¬°Corra la voz!</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/Decision2013_BD6_3-18-13.pdf">Baje un folleto para compartir con sus amigos y otros padres de familia.</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://www.facebook.com/ccsafamilies">Visitenos en Facebook!</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>¬øPor qu√© es importante la elecci√≥n del LAUSD para mi escuela p√∫blica ch√°rter?</h3>\n\n<p>Los siete miembros de la Junta Directiva del LAUSD:\n- Supervisan 763 escuelas tradicionales del distrito y <strong>210 escuelas ch√°rter</strong>.\nLa Junta del LAUSD decide:\n- Si se renovar√° el permiso a nuestras escuelas o se cerrar√°n.\n- Qu√© edificios escolares y aulas tendr√°n nuestras escuelas ch√°rter.\n- Si una nueva escuela ch√°rter puede abrir.\n- Y vigilan c√≥mo operan nuestras escuelas ch√°rter, desde los programas de educaci√≥n especial hasta el presupuesto.\nSus decisiones afectan a m√°s de <strong>664,000 estudiantes en Los √Ångeles</strong>.\n¬øLa nueva junta directiva representar√° lo que ustedes quieren para <strong>sus escuelas</strong> y <strong>sus hijos</strong>?</p>\n\n<h3>Los Candidatos para la Junta Directiva (Board District 6)</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Antonio Sanchez</li>\n<li>Monica Ratliff</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Fechas clave</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>22 de abril - Primer d√≠a para registrarse para votar por correo</li>\n<li>6 de mayo - Fecha l√≠mite de inscripci√≥n de votantes</li>\n<li>14 de mayo - Ultimo d√≠a para registrarse para votar por correo</li>\n<li>21 de mayo- ¬°D√≠a de la elecci√≥n!\n¬°Todos los votos cuentan!</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>¬°USTED decide el futuro de Los √Ångeles!</h3>\n\n<p>Todos los d√≠as, los funcionarios electos toman decisiones importantes que afectan a nuestras escuelas y a nuestros hijos. Cuando los padres participan y hablan, los  pol√≠ticos escuchan. Por eso es que es TAN importante para nosotros que usted vote. ¬°Su voto es su voz!</p>\n\n<h2>1. Reg√≠strese para votar</h2>\n\n<p>Recoja una forma para registrarse como votante en la oficina de elecciones de su condado, en la biblioteca o en la Oficina del Servicio Postal de Estados Unidos. Tambi√©n puede registrarse por internet en el sitio del Secretario de Estado: www.sos.ca.gov. ¬°Reg√≠strese antes del 26 de febrero!</p>\n\n<h2>2. Inf√≥rmese</h2>\n\n<p>¬°Aprenda m√°s sobre los candidatos! Families That Can publicar√° las Gu√≠as de los Candidatos y organizar√° un Foro de Candidatos en los tres distritos de la junta directiva del LAUSD en febrero. Usted puede encontrar siempre las noticias m√°s recientes en:\nwww.familiesthatcan.org/la2013\nReg√≠strese en www.familiesthatcan.org para obtener las noticias m√°s  recientes sobre las elecciones  2013 del LAUSD ¬°a trav√©s de su correo electr√≥nico!</p>\n\n<h2>3. Vote el 21 de mayo!</h2>\n\n<p>¬°Queremos ense√±arle a nuestros estudiantes a ser buenos ciudadanos! ¬°Empecemos por poner un buen ejemplo y salgamos a votar el 21 de mayo!</p>\n', 'Elecci√≥n para la Junta Directiva del LAUSD en el 21 de mayo', 'En el 21 de mayo, los votantes del este del Valle de San Fernando tienen la oportunidad para votar por su representante en la Junta Directiva del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Los √Ångeles (LAUSD).  ¬°Aprenda como se puede involucrarse para tener un impacto!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '185-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:20', '2016-01-13 04:22:20', '', 185, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/185-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1011, 3, '2016-01-13 04:22:21', '2016-01-13 04:22:21', '<p>Candidate forums are a great way to hear first-hand from the people running for school board - attend one in your area! Families That Can is hosting forums in February, dates coming soon.\nThere are forums hosted by the United Way in partnership with many community organizations coming up soon.</p>\n\n<h3>LAUSD School Board District 4</h3>\n\n<p>Thursday January 24, 2013\nVenice Boys and Girls Club\n2232 Lincoln Blvd. Venice, CA 90291\n5:30 PM - 7:30 PM\nInvited:  Candidates Kate Anderson &amp; Board Member Steve Zimmer</p>\n\n<h3>LAUSD School Board District 6</h3>\n\n<p>Thursday January 31, 2013\nBoys and Girls Club of San Fernando Valley\n11251 Glenoaks Blvd. Paicoma, CA 91331\n5:30 PM - 7:30 PM\nInvited: Candidates Maria Cano, Monica Ratliff, Antonio Sanchez, Iris Zuniga\nModerated discussion open to parents, students and community members. Food, Childcare and Translation Provided\nReserve a space or to submit questions call 213-808-6407\nor e-mail or <a href="mailto:rsmith@unitedwayla.org">rsmith@unitedwayla.org</a>.\nSponsored by:\n- United Way of Greater Los Angeles\n- Alliance for A Better Community\n- Educate Our State\n- Families In Schools\n- Lanai Road Elementary Action Committee\n- LA Chamber of Commerce\n- LA Urban League\n- Leadership for Education Equity\n- NAACP LA\n- National Council of La Raza\n- Project Grad Los Angeles\n- Southern Christian Leadership Conference LA\n- Venice Neighborhood Council Education Committee\n- Youth Speak Collective</p>\n', 'United Way and Community Organizations Host LAUSD Candidate Forums this January', 'Candidate forums are a great way to hear first-hand from the people running for school board - attend one in your area! Families That Can is hosting forums in February, dates coming soon.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '184-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:22:21', '2016-01-13 04:22:21', '', 184, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/184-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1012, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:34', '2016-01-13 04:24:34', '<p>Si usted vive en Los √Ångeles, quiz√°s la cosa m√°s importante que puede hacer para usted mismo, sus hijos y el movimiento de las escuelas ch√°rter es votar en la elecci√≥n de la junta escolar el martes, 3 de marzo. ¬øSabe qui√©nes son los candidatos que est√°n tratando de representar a usted?  Visite <a href="http://www.ccsaadvocates.org/">Los Defensores de CCSA</a> para saber m√°s de la elecci√≥n.  ¬°Y por favor vote el martes!</p>\n', '¬°Por favor, por favor vote el martes!', '¬øSabe usted por qui√©n va a votar para la elecci√≥n de la junta escolar de L.A.?\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '343-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:34', '2016-01-13 04:24:34', '', 343, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/343-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1013, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Granada_Hills _Charter_High_Wins_Decathlon_Feb_2015.jpg" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/Granada%20Hills%20Charter%20High%20Wins%20Decathlon.jpg" width="536" height="400" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nGranada Hills Charter High School beat nearly 60 teams in the L.A. Unified Academic Decathlon, setting a record for any regional, state or national competition in the U.S. Academic Decathlon\'s 47-year history. "Every year, I tell people this is the best group of kids I\'ve ever seen and I\'m always right," Cliff Ker, who coordinates the decathlon, told the Daily News. "This is by far the best group overall of students I\'ve ever seen here." Read all about it in the <a href="http://www.dailynews.com/social-affairs/20150213/granada-hills-charter-high-school-wins-lausds-academic-decathlon-competition">Daily News story</a>.</p>\n', 'L.A. Charter School Wins Decathlon', 'It was a record-setting victory for Granada Hills Charter High School!\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '342-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '', 342, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/342-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1014, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Richmond_Parent_Choice_Weekend_Feb_2015.jpeg (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2015/02/Richmond Parent Choice Weekend-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nIf you\'re a parent in Richmond who\'s interested in charter schools, chances are you spent February 7th at Parent Choice Weekend. The event drew more than 500 people, including representatives from every one of the area\'s 11 charter schools. Folks learned about their education options and also enjoyed a series of student performances.  More than a dozen community organizations that provide tutoring, after school activities and other enrichment opportunities were on hand as well. It was a great chance for families to get to know their local charter schools - and each other too!</p>\n', 'Parent Choice Weekend Draws 500 Attendees', 'Support for charter schools is booming in Richmond, where neighbors recently gathered to learn more about their education options.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '341-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '', 341, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/341-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1015, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Valiente_hearing_LACOE_Feb_2015.JPG (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2015/02/Valiente photo-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nFamilies in Southeast L.A. were disappointed last year when the school board prevented <a href="http://www.valientecollegeprep.org/">Valiente College Preparatory Charter School</a> from opening its doors, purely because of politics. But instead of giving up, they fought back. So earlier this month, when Valiente founder Jacob Wertz asked the L.A. County Board of Education to approve the school, families and students were right beside him. They made it clear that the community wants a new charter school that will hold students to high standards and help them graduate ready for college and career.\nAnd guess what? They succeeded. The County gave Valiente the green light to open this fall. Check out this <a href="https://www.facebook.com/video.php?v=10153063075294919&amp;set=vb.185113054918&amp;type=2&amp;theater">news story on Telemundo</a>, whose cameras were on hand to cover Valiente\'s victory. Go families!</p>\n', 'Families Triumph with New Charter School', 'When politics prevented LAUSD from approving Valiente College Prep, parents and students didn\'t take no for an answer.\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '340-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '', 340, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/340-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1016, 3, '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '<p><figure class="figure-full figure-border"><img alt="Latino_girls_stock_photo.jpg (Homepage Slideshow)" src="http://www.ccsafamilies.org/assets_c/2015/02/breakfastdsc_3700-cropped-proto-ccsa_families_theme___home_slideshow_large.jpg" width="690" height="372" class="mt-image-none" style="" /></figure>\nIf you live in Los Angeles, perhaps the most important thing you can do for you, your children and the charter school movement is to vote in the school board election on Tuesday, March 3rd. Do you know the candidates who are running to represent you? Visit <a href="http://www.ccsaadvocates.org/">CCSA Advocates</a> to find out more about the election. And please vote on Tuesday!</p>\n', 'Please, Please Vote on Tuesday!', 'Do you know who you\'re voting for in the L.A. school board election?\n', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '339-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '2016-01-13 04:24:35', '', 339, 'http://dev.ccsafamilies.org/339-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
